name: unencapsulated tactile receptor
description: Free nerve endings are widely distributed throughout the body, and are found as branches of unmyelinated, or lightly myelinated fibres grouped in bundles beneath the epithelium. As they penetrate the epithelium, they lose their myelin, and branch among the epithelial cells. Branches of one nerve may cover a wide area and overlap the territories of other nerves. The free nerve endings detect pain, touch, pressure and temperature, and are associated with C fibres.

name: anterior mediastinal lymph node
description: A lymph node located in the superior mediastinum that collects lymph from the thymus, the pericardium, and the right side of the heart.

name: anterior surface of prostate
description: The aspect of the prostate facing the pubic symphysis.

name: superficial fibular nerve
description: A branch of the common fibular nerve that innervates the fibularis longus and brevis muscles, and via branches innervates parts of the dorsal part of the pes.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001324|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0001387|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0002387|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0010526|RO:0002380 some UBERON:0001324|UBERON:0003431|UBERON:0035652

name: basal vein
description: The basal vein is formed at the anterior perforated substance by the union of (a) a small anterior cerebral vein which accompanies the anterior cerebral artery and supplies the medial surface of the frontal lobe by the fronto-basal vein. (b) the deep middle cerebral vein (deep Sylvian vein), which receives tributaries from the insula and neighboring gyri, and runs in the lower part of the lateral cerebral fissure, and (c) the inferior striate veins, which leave the corpus striatum through the anterior perforated substance. The basal vein passes backward around the cerebral peduncle, and ends in the internal cerebral vein; it receives tributaries from the interpeduncular fossa, the inferior horn of the lateral ventricle, the hippocampal gyrus, and the mid-brain.

name: deep middle cerebral vein
description: The blood vessel that receives deoxygenated blood from the insula and gyri and drains into the basal vein of Rosenthal deep in the lateral sulcus.

name: body of gallbladder
description: The middle portion of the gallbladder which is distal to the gallbladder neck and proximal to the gallbladder fundus.

name: esophageal artery
description: Any of several arteries that arise from the aorta and supply blood to the esophagus.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001515|RO:0002170 some UBERON:0002345|RO:0002178 some UBERON:0001043|RO:0002380 some UBERON:0001515|UBERON:0003834|UBERON:0004573

name: upper inner quadrant of breast
description: The quarter of the breast which is superior and medial.

name: deep lymphatic vessel
description: The tubules that carry lymph throughout the body that are in the interior of the body or limbs.

name: posterior ciliary vein
description: The outer layer of the choroid (lamina vasculosa) consists, in part, of the larger branches of the short ciliary arteries which run forward between the veins, before they bend inward to end in the capillaries, but is formed principally of veins, named, from their arrangement, the vorticose veins. They converge to four or five equidistant trunks, which pierce the sclera about midway between the sclero-corneal junction and the entrance of the optic nerve. They drain uveal tract.

name: vasculature of integument
description: The part of the circulatory system that lies within the subcutaneous tissue layers close to the surface of the skin.

name: superficial vein
description: Any of the veins carrying deoxygenated blood from the subcutaneous tissue layers.

name: deep vein
description: A blood vessel carrying deoxygenated blood far beneath the skin usually accompanying an artery.

name: left cardiac chamber
description: Any chamber of the left side of the heart.

name: right cardiac chamber
description: Any chamber of the right side of the heart.

name: magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus
description: A nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is characterized by large widely scattered cells.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2000687|RO:0002160 some NCBITaxon:32443|RO:0002162 some (not (NCBITaxon:27686))|RO:0002162 some (not (NCBITaxon:7900))|UBERON:0006569|UBERON:0035568

name: parvocellular superficial pretectal nucleus
description: A nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is characterized by small cells.

name: caudal pretectal nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the superficial pretectum and is rostrally contiguous with the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus. Cells of the caudal pretectal nucleus are slightly smaller and less orderly around a central neuropil than those of the magnocellular superficial pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: central pretectal nucleus
description: Any nucleus found in the central pretectum.

name: accessory pretectal nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus that is part of the central pretectum and lies dorsolateral to the caudal pretectal nucleus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: periventricular pretectal nucleus
description: A nucleus medial to the central pretectal nucleus in the periventricular zone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001944|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2000293|RO:0002162 some (not (NCBITaxon:40674))|UBERON:0006569|UBERON:0014450

name: circular nucleus of antherior hypothalamic nucleus
description: A group of cells located in the central part of the anterior hypothalamic nucleus in the anterior hypothalamic region of the rat ( Swanson-2004 ) and the mouse ( Paxinos-2001 ). Functionally it belongs to the magnocellular neuroendocrine cell groups of the subcortical motor system ( Swanson-2004 ).

name: profundal placode
description: An embryonic structure positioned halfway between the prospective eye and ear, adjacent to the future midbrain-hindbrain boundary. The profundal and the trigeminal ganglia are separate distally but fused at their proximal end as they condense around NF stage 24.

name: accessory nerve cord of dorsal region
description: Any longitudinally extending condensed cluster of neurons and processes that runs along the dorsal mid-line of the animal that is not the most prominent nerve cord.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001137|BSPO:0005001 some UBERON:0001137|RO:0002162 some (not (NCBITaxon:7711))|UBERON:0011215

name: outer root sheath companion layer
description: The innermost layer of the outer root sheath.

name: peripharyngeal space
description: The space filled with loose areolar tissue surrounding the pharynx; it is divided into two major divisions, the parapharyngeal space and the retropharyngeal space.

name: parapharyngeal space
description: The portion of the peripharyngeal space limited by the lateral wall of the pharynx, the cervical vertebrae and medial pterygoid muscle.

name: retropharyngeal space
description: The portion of the peripharyngeal space that is located posterior to the pharynx.

name: quadrant of breast
description: The part of the breast that is bordered by the intermammary line and a perpendicular line bisecting the nipple.

name: ocular adnexa
description: The parts of the orbital region that are outside of the the eyeball, including the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.

name: laryngeal nerve
description: Any nerve that innervates the larynx.

name: anterior superior alveolar nerve
description: The anterior superior alveolar branch (anterior superior dental branch), of considerable size, is given off from the maxillary nerve just before its exit from the infraorbital foramen; it descends in a canal in the anterior wall of the maxillary sinus, and divides into branches which supply the incisor and canine teeth. It communicates with the middle superior alveolar branch, and gives off a nasal branch, which passes through a minute canal in the lateral wall of the inferior meatus, and supplies the mucous membrane of the anterior part of the inferior meatus and the floor of the nasal cavity, communicating with the nasal branches from the sphenopalatine ganglion.

name: posterior auricular nerve
description: A branch of the facial nerve that innervates the posterior auricular and intrinsic muscles of the auricle and, through its occipital branch, innervates the occipital belly of the occipitofrontal muscle.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003725|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0001757|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0010946|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0018110|RO:0002380 some UBERON:0003725|UBERON:0035648

name: nerve innervating pinna
description: Any nerve that innervates the pinna.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001647|CARO:0001001|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0001757|RO:0002380 some UBERON:0001647|UBERON:0011779

name: nerve of penis
description: Any nerve that innervates the penis.

name: nerve of clitoris
description: Any nerve that innervates the clitoris.

name: fibular nerve
description: Any nerve that innervates the fibularis. Includes the common fibular nerve, and its branches.

name: paraumbilical vein
description: The small superficial veins that arise from the cutaneous veins, and run from the umbilicus along the round ligament of the liver; these terminate as accessory portal veins in the liver.
parents: BFO:0000050 some RO:0002577|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000916|RO:0002170 some UBERON:0001639|UBERON:0013126

name: deep facial vein
description: The anterior facial vein receives a branch of considerable size, the deep facial vein, from the pterygoid venous plexus.

name: anterior facial vein
description: A vein that represents a continuation of the angular vein and lies behind the facial artery.

name: capillary plexus
description: A network of capillaries.

name: subsegmental lymph node
description: The lymph nodes around the subsegmental bronchi.

name: median lobe of prostate
description: The upper, smaller part of the prostate between the ejaculatory ducts and the urethra.

name: coccygeal nerve plexus
description: The coccygeal plexus is a plexus of nerves near the coccyx bone.

name: inferior mesenteric nerve plexus
description: The inferior mesenteric plexus is derived chiefly from the aortic plexus. It surrounds the inferior mesenteric artery, and divides into a number of secondary plexuses, which are distributed to all the parts supplied by the artery, viz. , the left colic and sigmoid plexuses, which supply the descending and sigmoid parts of the colon; and the superior hemorrhoidal plexus, which supplies the rectum and joins in the pelvis with branches from the pelvic plexuses.
parents: BFO:0000050 some RO:0002577|CARO:0001001|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0001052|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0001158|RO:0002134 some UBERON:0001159|UBERON:0035771|obo:uberon/core#extends_fibers_into some UBERON:0035772

name: abdominal nerve plexus
description: The abdominal aortic plexus (aortic plexus) is formed by branches derived, on either side, from the celiac plexus and ganglia, and receives filaments from some of the lumbar ganglia. It is situated upon the sides and front of the aorta, between the origins of the superior and inferior mesenteric arteries. From this plexus arise part of the spermatic, the inferior mesenteric, and the hypogastric plexuses; it also distributes filaments to the inferior vena cava.

name: thoracic aortic plexus
description: The thoracic aortic plexus is a sympathetic plexus in the region of the thoracic aorta.

name: submandibular region
description: The region between the mandible and the hyoid bone that contains the submandibular and sublingual glands, suprahyoid muscles, submandibular ganglion, and lingual artery.

name: telencephalic song nucleus HVC
description: A nucleus in the brain of songbirds located in the caudal nidopallium, projecting to the song motor pathway via the robust nucleus of the arcopallium and to the Anterior Forebrain Pathway via the basal ganglia nucleus Area X.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0007334|RO:0002160 some NCBITaxon:9126|RO:0002216 some GO:0098583|UBERON:0009663

name: alveus of CA2 field
description: Part of alveus lying within hippocampal sector CA2.

name: extrapyramidal tract system
description: A neural network located in the brain that is part of the motor system involved in the coordination of movement that is distinct from the pyramidal tract.

name: future mouth
description: The primordial mouth region of the developing head.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0007026|BFO:0000051 some UBERON:0000925|BFO:0000051 some UBERON:0000930|CARO:0000000|UBERON:0013522

name: muscle layer of sigmoid colon
description: A muscle layer that is part of the sigmoid colon.

name: robust nucleus of arcopallium
description: A specialized nucleus within the intermediate archistriatum of songbirds, required for and active during the production of learned song.

name: pericardial fat
description: The sum of epicardial and paracardial fat deposits.

name: abdominopelvic cavity
description: The part of the ventral body cavity that is within the abdominal segment of the trunk, which encompasses the abdomen proper plus pelvic cavity.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002323|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002417|CARO:0000000|RO:0002572 some UBERON:0002417|UBERON:0000464

name: peritoneal sac
description: A serous sac that is the aggregate of the peritoneum and the peritoneal cavity, located in the abdominal cavity.
parents: BFO:0000051 some UBERON:0001179|BFO:0000051 some UBERON:0002358|RO:0001025 some UBERON:0003684|UBERON:0002075|UBERON:0005906

name: left adrenal gland cortex
description: The thick outer layer of the adrenal gland that is in the left side of the abdomen.

name: left adrenal gland medulla
description: The adrenal gland medulla that is in the left side of the abdomen.

name: right adrenal gland cortex
description: The thick outer layer of the adrenal gland that is in the right side of the abdomen.

name: right adrenal gland medulla
description: The adrenal gland medulla that is in the right side of the abdomen.

name: right gastroepiploic artery
description: Artery that runs from right to left along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, anastomosing with the left gastroepiploic branch of the splenic artery.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0010132|RO:0002178 some UBERON:0002108|RO:0002380 some UBERON:0010132|UBERON:0004573|UBERON:0009025

name: left gastroepiploic artery
description: Artery that runs from left to right along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, and anastomoses with the right gastroepiploic.

name: costal diaphragm
description: The domain of the diaphragm that is a thin domed sheet of muscle composed of a radial array of myofibers extending laterally from the ribs and medially to a central tendon.
parents: BFO:0000050 some RO:0002577|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001103|BSPO:0000126 some UBERON:0001103|CARO:0000003|RO:0002371 some UBERON:0006670|UBERON:0000063|UBERON:0015212

name: apical region of left ventricle
description: Region around the apex of the cardiac left ventricle located at the bottom of the left ventricle inferior to both the mitral and aortic valve.

name: esophagogastric junction mucosa
description: Mucosa from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: esophagogastric junction submucosa
description: Submucosa from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: esophagogastric junction muscularis mucosa
description: Muscularis mucosa from the lowest portion of the esophagus, just proximal to the stomach.

name: infraorbital margin
description: The infraorbital margin is the lower margin of the orbita.

name: orbital margin
description: The mostly sharp edge of the orbital opening that is the peripheral border of the base of the pyramidal orbit.

name: frontomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the frontal bone and the frontal process of the maxilla.

name: zygomaticomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the zygomatic bone and the zygomatic process of the maxilla.

name: ethmoidomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the orbital surface of the body of the maxilla with the orbital plate of the ethmoid bone.

name: sphenomaxillary suture
description: An inconstant suture between the pterygoid process of the sphenoid bone and the body of the maxilla.

name: lacrimomaxillary suture
description: A suture between the lacrimal bone and the maxilla.

name: intraculminate fissure of cerebellum
description: A fissure that divides the culmen lobule (lobules IV and V).
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0007763|RO:0002220 some UBERON:0004077|RO:0002220 some UBERON:0004079|UBERON:0003980

name: radiation of corpus callosum
description: The spreading out of the fibers of the corpus callosum in the centrum semiovale of each cerebral hemisphere.

name: paracentral lobule
description: The junction of the precentral gyrus and postcentral gyrus on the medial surface of the cerebral cortex. It lies across the boundary between the frontal lobe and the parietal lobe.

name: Meyer's loop of optic radiation
description: Part of the optic radiation which sweeps back on itself into the temporal lobe, just lateral to the temporal horn of the lateral ventricle.

name: arcuate fasciculus
description: The arcuate fasciculus (Latin, curved bundle) is the neural pathway connecting the posterior part of the temporoparietal junction with the frontal cortex in the brain and is now considered as part of the Superior longitudinal fasciculus.

name: amiculum
description: A dense surrounding coat of white fibers, as the sheath of the inferior olive and of the dentate nucleus.

name: epididymal lumen
description: The lumen of the epididymis.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001301|CARO:0000000|RO:0001019 some UBERON:0006530|RO:0002572 some UBERON:0001301|UBERON:0000464

name: velum feeding organ
description: The locomotory and feeding organ, found in the larval veliger stage of bivalves.

name: supravaginal part of cervix
description: Supravaginal portion of cervix: the part of the cervix uteri that does not protrude into the vagina.

name: epithelial lining fluid
description: Epithelial lining fluid forms a thin fluid layer that covers the mucosa of the alveoli, the small airways, and the large airways.

name: promontory of tympanic cavity
description: The promontory of the tympanic cavity, better known as the cochlear promontory is a rounded hollow prominence, formed by the projection outward of the first turn of the cochlea. It is placed between the fenestrae, and is furrowed on its surface by small grooves, for the lodgement of branches of the tympanic plexus. A minute spicule of bone frequently connects the promontory to the pyramidal eminence.

name: scleral lamina cribrosa
description: The perforated part of the sclera through which pass the axons of the retinal ganglion cells.

name: alveolar mucosa
description: The mucous membrane apical to the attached gingiva.

name: encapsulated tactile receptor
description: A tacile mechanoreceptor that lacks a capsule.

name: calcar avis of the lateral ventricle
description: On the medial wall of the posterior cornu of the lateral ventricle is a longitudinal eminence, the calcar avis (hippocampus minor), which is an involution of the ventricular wall produced by the calcarine fissure. It is sometimes visible on ultrasonogram.

name: postsubiculum
description: Division of subicular cortex characterized by projections from the anterodorsal thalamic nucleus and to a lesser extent the anteroventral nucleus, bordered ventrally and laterally by the presubiculum and dorsally and medially by the retrosplenial granular a cortex.. The border is characterized by an abrupt change in the cyto- and chemoarchitecture.

name: interanterodorsal nucleus of the thalamus
description: A group of nerve cells that bridges the midline of the thalamus between the anterodorsal nucleus of the thalamus of the left and right sides. According to Crosby (1962), it is more developed and consistently present in rodents than in primates (adapted from Brain Info).

name: nucleus incertus
description: Distinct cell group in caudoventral regions of the pontine periventricular gray, adjacent to the ventromedial border of the caudal dorsal tegmental nucleus.

name: accessory abducens nucleus
description: A small cluster of neurons in the pontine reticular formation in some mammals, containing the majority of motoneurons innervating thenretractor bulbi muscles of the eye.

name: bed nucleus of the accessory olfactory tract
description: A group of cells near the surface of the brain between the supraoptic nucleus and the cortical amygdalar nucleus in the rat ( Swanson-1998 ) and the mouse ( Paxinos-2001 ). It is one of five subdivisions of the medial amygdalar nucleus.

name: dopaminergic cell groups
description: Collections of neurons in the central nervous system that have been demonstrated by histochemical fluorescence to contain the neurotransmitter dopamine ( Fuxe-1970 ).

name: A13 dopaminergic cell group
description: A group of cells that fluoresce for dopamine and are distributed in clusters that, in the primate, are ventral and medial to the mammillothalamic tract of the hypothalamus; a few extend into the reuniens nucleus of the thalamus (Felten-1983). In the mouse A13 is located ventral to the mammillothalamic tract of the thalamus in the zona incerta (adapted from Brain Info).

name: intergluteal cleft
description: The line that divided the gluteal regions of the body.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001137|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002355|RO:0002220 some UBERON:0013691|UBERON:0006800

name: gluteal sulcus
description: A horizontal crease formed by the inferior aspect of the buttocks and the posterior upper leg.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001137|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002355|RO:0002150 some UBERON:0002103|RO:0002150 some UBERON:0013691|UBERON:0007651

name: honey
description: A sweet viscid material elaborated out of the nectar of flowers in the honey sac of various bees.

name: subglottis
description: The lower portion of the larynx, extending from just beneath the vocal cords down to the top of the trachea.

name: tracheoesophageal fold
description: One of two longitudinal ridges that develop caudal to the pharynx and fuses to give rise to the tracheoesophageal septum.

name: tracheoesophageal septum
description: The tracheoesophageal septum is formed from the tracheoesophageal folds which fuse in the midline to form a structure called tracheoesophageal septum. It divides the esophagus from the trachea. It divides the foregut tube into the laryngotracheal tube ventrally and esophagus dorsally. Developmental abnormalities can lead to a tracheoesophageal fistula.
parents: RO:0002150 some UBERON:0001043|RO:0002150 some UBERON:0003126|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0036069|RO:0002494 some UBERON:0036069|UBERON:0003037|UBERON:0004120

name: vein of vestibular aqueduct
description: A vein that leaves the vestibule through an individual bone canal running parallel to the vestibular aqueduct up to the dura of the posterior side of the petrosa in the area of the endolymphatic sac. It then opens in the inferior petrosal sinus or the jugular bulb. The vein receives other branches from the bone, dura and sac.
parents: BFO:0000050 some RO:0002577|RO:0002376 some UBERON:0001641|RO:0002376 some UBERON:0005475|RO:0002376 some UBERON:0007160|UBERON:0001638

name: meningeal branch of mandibular nerve
description: The meningeal branch of the mandibular nerve (recurrent branch, nervus spinosus) is a branch of the mandibular nerve that supplies the dura mater.

name: incisive duct
description: An infrequent rudimentary duct, or protrusion of the mucous membrane into the incisive canal, on either side of the anterior extremity of the nasal crest.

name: glymphatic system
description: Macroscopic waste clearance system that utilizes a unique system of perivascular tunnels, formed by astroglial cells, to promote efficient elimination of soluble proteins and metabolites from the central nervous system.

name: ambient gyrus
description: A rostral part of the parahippocampal gyrus.

name: palmaris brevis
description: The Palmaris brevis is a thin, quadrilateral muscle, placed beneath the integument of the ulnar side of the hand. It arises by tendinous fasciculi from the transverse carpal ligament and palmar aponeurosis; the fleshy fibers are inserted into the skin on the ulnar border of the palm of the hand. The muscle is innervated by the superficial branch of the ulnar nerve, containing fibers from the eighth cervical and first thoracic nerves.

name: abductor digiti minimi of hand
description: The Abductor minimi digiti (Abductor digiti quinti) is situated on the ulnar border of the palm of the hand. It arises from the pisiform bone and from the tendon of the Flexor carpi ulnaris, and ends in a flat tendon, which divides into two slips; one is inserted into the ulnar side of the base of the first phalanx of the little finger; the other into the ulnar border of the aponeurosis of the Extensor digiti quinti proprius. In case of polydactyly it may insert to the sixth finger instead, if there is one.

name: flexor digiti minimi brevis of hand
description: The flexor digiti minimi brevis is a muscle in the hand that flexes the little finger. It lies in the same plane as the abductor digiti minimi, on its radial side.

name: opponens digiti minimi of hand
description: The opponens minimi digiti (opponens digiti quinti in older texts) is a muscle in the hand. It is of a triangular form, and placed immediately beneath the palmaris brevis, abductor minimi digiti, and flexor brevis minimi digiti. It arises from the convexity of the hamulus of the hamate bone, and contiguous portion of the transverse carpal ligament; it is inserted into the whole length of the metacarpal bone of the little finger, along its ulnar margin.

name: Sertoli cell barrier
description: The blood-testis barrier (abbreviated as BTB) is a physical barrier between the blood vessels and the seminiferous tubules of the animal testes. The barrier is formed by tight connections between the Sertoli cells, which are sustentacular cells (supporting cells) of the seminiferous tubules, and nourish the spermatogonia. The barrier prevents passage of cytotoxic agents (bodies or substances that are toxic to cells) into the seminiferous tubules.

name: intertragic incisure
description: A surface structure that is the narrowed downward continuation of the conchal space bounded anteriorly by the borders of the tragus, posteriorly by theantitragus, and along its lower lateral margins and inferior boundary by the connection between the first two.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001757|CARO:0000000|RO:0002220 some UBERON:0010887|RO:0002220 some UBERON:0016467|UBERON:0006846

name: rectosigmoid junction
description: An anatomical junction that is between the sigmoid colon and rectum.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000160|RO:0002176 some UBERON:0001052|RO:0002176 some UBERON:0001159|UBERON:8410024

name: anatomical surface region
description: Material anatomical entity that forms the outermost boundary of an anatomical structure.

name: tympanic nerve
description: The tympanic nerve (nerve of Jacobson) is a branch of the glossopharyngeal nerve found near the ear.

name: coelomic fluid
description: A bodily fluid that is located in the coelom.

name: secondary prosencephalon
description: The most anterior region of the forebrain including both the telencephalon and the hypothalamus in the prosomeric model.

name: secretion of serous membrane
description: A transudate found in the serous sac.

name: incudostapedial joint
description: The small synovial joint connecting the inclus and the stapes, located between the lenticular process on the long crus of the incus and the head of the stapes.

name: incudomallear joint
description: The saddle-shaped synovial joint connecting the incus and the malleus.

name: joint of auditory ossicle
description: Any synovial joint that connects auditory ossicles.

name: zona pectinata of basilar membrane of cochlea
description: The acellular membrane that forms the outer two thirds of the basilar membrane of the conchlea.

name: interdigital space
description: The space between the digits of the hand or foot.

name: piriform aperture
description: A pear-shaped bony inlet comprising the most anterior and narrowest bony portion of the nasal airway.

name: iliac lymph sac
description: An embryonic lymph sac that forms near the junction of the iliac veins with the posterior cardinal veins.

name: embryonic cisterna chyli
description: An embryonic lymph sac that is dorsal to the retroperitoneal lymph sac, at the level of the adrenal glands.

name: uterine ligament
description: Any of the eight ligaments pertaining to the uterus including the anterior, posterior, lateral, sacro-uterine and round ligaments.

name: supraglottic part of larynx
description: The upper part of the larynx, including the epiglottis; the area above the vocal cords.

name: zygomaticotemporal nerve
description: The zygomaticotemporal nerve or zygomaticotemporal branch (temporal branch) is derived from the maxillary branch of the trigeminal nerve (Cranial nerve V). It runs along the lateral wall of the orbit in a groove in the zygomatic bone, receives a branch of communication from the lacrimal, and passes through zygomaticotemporal foramen in the zygomatic bone to enter the temporal fossa. It ascends between the bone, and substance of the Temporalis muscle, pierces the temporal fascia about 2.5 cm. above the zygomatic arch, and is distributed to the skin of the side of the forehead, and communicates with the facial nerve and with the auriculotemporal branch of the mandibular nerve. As it pierces the temporal fascia, it gives off a slender twig, which runs between the two layers of the fascia to the lateral angle of the orbit.

name: tonsillar pillar
description: The anterior and posterior borders of the tonsillar fossa. They are composed of muscle tissue.

name: wall of left ventricle
description: Wall of ventricle which is continuous with the wall of aorta.

name: wall of right ventricle
description: Wall of ventricle which is continuous with the wall of pulmonary trunk.

name: anterior wall of right ventricle
description: Region of wall of right ventricle which is continuous with the lateral and septal walls of right ventricle.

name: adnexa of uterus
description: The fallopian tubes and ovaries.

name: mucosa of lip
description: A mucosa that is part of a lip region [Automatically generated definition].

name: renal pelvis/ureter
description: The upper tract of the renal system. The renal pelvis is the large cavity in the middle of each kidney. Urine drains from each kidney through a long tube called the ureter, into the bladder, where it is stored until it is passed from the body through the urethra.

name: wall of heart
description: Wall of organ which has as its parts the endocardium, myocardium , epicardium, and the cardiac septum, surrounded by the pericardial sac proper and is continuous with the walls of the systemic and pulmonary arterial and venous trees.

name: primary hair
description: Very thin, soft, usually unpigmented, downy hair that is sometimes found on the body of a fetal or new-born human.

name: vellus hair
description: Short, thin, slight-colored, and barely noticeable hair that develops on most of a person's body during childhood.

name: terminal hair
description: Thick and long hair, as compared with vellus hair growing elsewhere.

name: waist
description: The part of the human abdomen below the ribs and above the hips, often narrower than the areas above and below.

name: paracardial gastric lymph node
description: Gastric lymph node located around the cardia of stomach.

name: subscapular axillary lymph node
description: An axillary lymph node that is placed along the lower margin of the posterior wall of the axilla in the course of the subscapular artery.

name: pectoral axillary lymph node
description: An axiallary lymph node along the lower border of the Pectoralis minor, in relation with the lateral thoracic artery. Their afferents drain the skin and muscles of the anterior and lateral thoracic walls, and the central and lateral parts of the mamma; their efferents pass partly to the central and partly to the subclavicular groups of axillary glands.

name: central axillary lymph node
description: An axillary lymph node that is imbedded in the adipose tissue near the base of the axilla.

name: apical axillary lymph node
description: An axillary lymph node that is situated partly posterior to the upper portion of the Pectoralis minor and partly above the upper border of this muscle.

name: inferior pancreatic lymph node
description: Pancreaticosplenioc lymph node located along the inferior margin of pancreas.

name: left gastric lymph node
description: Gastric lymph node located along the lesser curvature of stomach.
parents: BFO:0000050 some RO:0002577|BSPO:0000120 some UBERON:0000468|RO:0002170 some UBERON:0002508|UBERON:0015212|UBERON:0015863

name: superior left gastric lymph node
description: Left gastric lymph node located along the left gastric artery.

name: inferior left gastric lymph node
description: Left gastric lymph node located along the cardiac half of the lesser curvature of stomach in the lesser omentum.

name: common hepatic lymph node
description: Hepatic lymph node located along the common hepatic artery.

name: hepatoportal lymph node
description: Hepatic lymph node located along the portal vein.

name: proximal superior pancreatic lymph node
description: Superior pancreatic lymph node located along the proximal segment of splenic artery.

name: distal superior pancreatic lymph node
description: Superior pancreatic lymph node located along the distal segment of splenic artery.

name: anterior superior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node
description: Superior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node located on the anterior anterior of superior region of head of pancreas.

name: posterior superior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node
description: Superior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node located on the posterior aspect of superior portion of head of pancreas.

name: anterior inferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node
description: Inferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node located on the anterior aspect of inferior region of head of pancreas.

name: posterior inferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node
description: Inferior pancreaticoduodenal lymph node located on the posterior aspect of inferior region of head of pancreas.

name: visceral pre-aortic lymph node
description: Intestinal lymph node located anterior to aorta.

name: gastro-epiploic lymph node
description: Gastric lymph node located along the greater curvature of stomach.

name: craniocervical lymph node
description: Lymph node located in either head and neck region.

name: suprapyloric lymph node
description: Pylorioc lymph node located near the bifurcation of gastroduodenal artery and superior to the pylorus.

name: subpyloric lymph node
description: Pylorioc lymph node located in the angle between the superior and descending parts of duodenum.

name: bronchopulmonary lymph node
description: A tracheobronchial lymph node situated in the hilum of a lung.

name: anterior intercostal artery
description: The anterior intercostal branches of internal thoracic artery supply the upper five or six intercostal spaces.

name: accessory vertebral vein
description: A lower continuation of the vertebral vein and vertebral venous plexus that passes through the foramen of the transverse process of the 7th cervical vertebra and empties into the brachiocephalic vein.

name: anterior vertebral vein
description: A vein that commences in a plexus around the transverse processes of the upper cervical vertebr, descends in company with the ascending cervical artery between the Scalenus anterior and Longus capitis muscles, and opens into the terminal part of the vertebral vein.

name: suprascapular vein
description: The suprascapular vein is a vein running above the scapula. It empties into the external jugular vein.

name: superior laryngeal vein
description: The superior laryngeal vein is a vein which drains the larynx into the superior thyroid vein.

name: appendicular artery
description: An artery that commonly arises from the terminal branch of the ileocolic artery, or less commonly from the posterior cecal artery or an ileal artery.[1][2] It descends behind the termination of the ileum and enters the mesoappendix of the vermiform appendix. It runs near the free margin of the mesoappendix and ends in branches which supply the appendix.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001197|RO:0002178 some UBERON:0001154|RO:0002380 some UBERON:0001197|UBERON:0004573

name: cystic artery
description: An artery that supplies oxygenated blood to the cystic duct.

name: prepyloric vein
description: The prepyloric vein is the last connecting branch onto the right gastric vein, marking the end of the stomach, and draining the proximal part of the duodenum

name: conus artery
description: The conus artery is generally considered to be the first branch of the right coronary artery (RCA) in the right sinus of Valsalva. However, one study has shown that in approximately 50% of humans, the conus artery arises from a discrete ostium in the right sinus of Valsalva.

name: pubic vein
description: vein ascending the posterior aspect of the body of the pubis to drain into the inferior epigastric vein; this vein frequently (about 20% of patients) serves as an accessory or replaced obturator vein.

name: rima vulvae
description: The fissure between the labia majora

name: urethral vein
description: A vein that drains the urethra.

name: Alcock's canal
description: An anatomical conduit in the pelvis through which the internal pudendal artery, internal pudendal veins, and the pudendal nerve pass.

name: superficial dorsal vein of penis
description: A vein that drains the prepuce and skin of the penis, and, running backward in the subcutaneous tissue, inclines to the right or left, and opens into the corresponding superficial external pudendal vein, a tributary of the great saphenous vein..
parents: BFO:0000050 some RO:0002577|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000989|RO:0002179 some UBERON:0001331|RO:0002179 some UBERON:0001332|RO:0002376 some UBERON:0009049|UBERON:0039422

name: right ovarian vein
description: Ovarian vein, each instance of which is a tributary  of some inferior vena cava that drains the right pampiniform plexus of some broad ligament.

name: left ovarian vein
description: Ovarian vein, each instance of which is a tributary  of some left renal vein that drains the left pampiniform plexus of some broad ligament.

name: mole
description: A benign tumor on the skin, usually with darker pigment.

name: labial commissure
description: Anatomical structure consisting of either corner of the mouth.

name: skin of snout
description: A zone of skin that is part of the snout.

name: top of head
description: The top of the head.

name: skin of face
description: A zone of skin that is part of the face.

name: Zymbal's gland
description: A multilobulated modified sebaceous gland that is located at the base of the external ear, lined by stratified squamous epithelium, and secretes into the auditory canal.

name: spleen pulp
description: The parenchyma of the spleen, consisting of lymphocytes and macrophages. It lies between the splenic trabecula. Red pulp is the part suffused with blood and white pulp consists of areas of lymphatic tissue where there are sleeves of lymphocytes and macrophages.

name: parenchyma of spleen
description: A parenchyma that is part of a spleen.

name: Brachet's cleft
description: The visible division between epiblast and hypoblast in the gastrula. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: Kupffer's vesicle
description: Small but distinctive epithelial sac containing fluid, located midventrally posterior to the yolk cell or its extension, and transiently present during most of the segmentation period. Kimmel et al, 1995. Kupffer's vesicle has been compared to the mouse embryonic node. Drummond et al, 2005.

name: ball
description: The anterior round region of the yolk cell present after the yolk extension forms during the segmentation period. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: median fin fold
description: Surface structure that will develop into one of the median fins. Extends from dorsal surface of fish, caudal to the 8th somite, to the ventral surface ending at the caudal side of the vent.

name: myotome somite 14
description: Portion of somite 14 that gives rise to body wall muscle masses. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: dorsal actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium which is part of the dorsal fin fold.

name: polster
description: The hatching gland rudiment at the time it underlies the forebrain during the early segmentation period. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: somite 1
description: Anteriormost undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: somite 5
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk segment 5 or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: somite 26
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early tail segment 26 or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: ventral actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium which is part of the ventral fin fold.

name: yolk
description: Nutrient store for embryonic development in the form of semicrystalline phospholipoprotein and contained within yolk granules. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: yolk syncytial layer
description: Peripheral layer of the yolk cell including nuclei and non-yolky cytoplasm. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: actinotrichium
description: Elastoidin fin ray that is slender, sometimes branched distally and present in the embryonic fin fold. Actinotrichia are translucent and exhibit birefringence.

name: apical ectodermal ridge dorsal fin
description: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the dorsal fin.

name: dorsal fin fold
description: Region of the median fin fold that develops into the dorsal fin.

name: extension
description: The posterior elongated region of the yolk cell that forms during the segmentation period. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: lateral line ganglion
description: Ganglion that develops from a cranial ectodermal placode and contains sensory neurons that innervate a lateral line.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002540|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0009128|UBERON:0001714|UBERON:0004121|obo:uberon/core#extends_fibers_into some UBERON:0008906

name: mandibular lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the mandibular lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.).

name: otic lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the otic lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.).

name: somite 20
description: Undifferentiated mesodermal component of early trunk or tail segment 20 or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: somite 30
description: Posteriormost undifferentiated mesodermal component of early tail segment or metamere, derived from paraxial mesoderm; forms the myotome, sclerotome and perhaps dermatome. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: anterior macula
description: Macula that is located in the developing anterior inner ear, and gives rise to the macula utricle. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.).

name: posterior lateral line nerve
description: Cranial nerve which enters the brain between cranial nerves VIII and IX; contains afferents and sensory efferents to the posterior lateral line ganglion and middle ganglion. Fibers from the posterior lateral line ganglion innervate the occipital dorsal lateral line and trunk lateral lines.

name: commissura rostral, pars ventralis
description: Part of the anterior commissure which abuts the preoptic region dorsally.

name: dorsal hypohyal bone
description: Replacement bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with the anterior ceratohyal posteriorly and the ventral hypohyal bone ventrally.
parents: RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001843|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001845|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001847|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0011610|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0011612|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0010314

name: efferent portion of pharyngeal arch artery
description: A section of a pharyngeal arch artery that carries blood away from the gills.
parents: BFO:0000050 some RO:0002577|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0004363|RO:0002179 some UBERON:0011150|RO:0002380 some UBERON:0004363|UBERON:0003469|UBERON:0003496|UBERON:0009141

name: infraorbital 1
description: Infraorbital in fishes that is the first (anteriormost) bone of the infraorbital series.

name: quadrate ventral process
description: Process that is the ventral, posteriorly-oriented bony extension of the quadrate.

name: lateral ethmoid bone
description: Endochondral bone that separates the olfactory region from the orbit, extends medially to meet its fellow medially below the frontal bones and is bordered by the mesethmoid anteriorly. It may articulate with the autopalatine and infraorbital 1 laterally. The lateral ethmoid is paired.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002241|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003112|RO:0002131 some UBERON:0001703|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001608|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001679|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001941|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2002032|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0006604|RO:0002473 some UBERON:0002481|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0010314|UBERON:0011164|UBERON:4300111

name: macula neglecta
description: Macula positioned on the floor of the utricle adjacent to the utriculosaccular foramen at the base of the common crus.

name: mesocoracoid bone
description: Endochondral bone that articulates laterally with the medial surface of the cleithrum and ventro-medially with the scapula and coracoid. Meoscoracoid bone is a small, arch-like bone that develops from the mesocoracoid cartilage. Mesocoracoid bone is paired.

name: metapterygoid
description: Endochondral bone that forms the posteriormost element of the palatal complex. It overlies the quadrate and symplectic, posteriorly it articulates with the hyomandibula and anteriorly with the entopterygoid and ectopterygoid. It curves dorsally to form the posteroventral surface of the orbit. The metapterygoid is paired.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011085|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001803|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001979|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0004752|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0011597

name: opercle
description: Dermal bone that forms the postero-dorsal part of the opercular series. The opercle articulates with the hyomandibula antero-dorsally and with the subopercle ventrally. The opercle is a paired bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011152|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2000555|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2001875|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001710|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2002282|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2005265|UBERON:0008907

name: mandibular lateral line
description: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva consisting of 2 neuromast. One neuromast is positioned at the front edge of the jaw the second posteriorly on the mandible. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.).

name: preopercle
description: Dermal bone that is part of the opercular series and bears the preopercular sensory canal. The preopercle is a paired bone and typically L-shaped, with the horizontal limb overlying the interopercle and the vertical limb overlying the opercle.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011152|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2000555|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2001875|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2002282|UBERON:0008907

name: anal fin proximal radial bone
description: Anal fin proximal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: radial bone
description: Radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: subopercle
description: Dermal bone that is part of the opercular series, lying below the opercle. The subopercle is paired and is typically a thin bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011152|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2000555|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2001875|UBERON:0008907

name: preopercle horizontal limb
description: A dermal bone that is the lower, horizontal portion of the preopercle bone.

name: medial octavolateralis nucleus
description: Lateral line sensory nucleus located in the cerebellum that processes sensory input from the lateral line.

name: ventral hypohyal bone
description: Replacement bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with the ceratohyal bone posteriorly and the dorsal hypohyal bone dorsally.
parents: RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001844|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001845|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001846|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001848|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0011610|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0011612|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0010314

name: external yolk syncytial layer
description: The portion of the YSL that is outside of the blastoderm margin during epiboly. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: brainstem and spinal white matter
description: CNS white matter that is part of the brain stem or spinal cord.

name: preopercle vertical limb
description: A dermal bone that is the upper, vertical portion of the preopercle bone.

name: basioccipital posterodorsal region
description: Endochondral bone which is the posterodorsal region of the basioccipital bone.

name: exoccipital posteroventral region
description: Endochondral bone which is the posterodorsal region of the exoccipital bone.

name: epipleural
description: Epipleurals lie below the horizontal septum and are posteroventrally directed. There are ossified epipleurals in certain ostariophysans. In many lower elopocephalan teleosts including ostariophysans the epipleural bones develop an anterodorsal branch so that they are forked proximally.

name: gill raker
description: Dermal bone that is a projection present on the inner surface of a branchial arch.

name: hypobranchial bone
description: Replacement bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates medially with a median skeletal element and laterally with a ceratobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: hypural
description: Laterally flattened haemal spine of an ural vertebra that lacks its arch and supports a few principal caudal lepidotrichia distally. A hypural may articulate or fuse with its ural centrum proximally or may lie ventral to the notochord. A hypural is an unpaired median bone that ossifies perichondrally. (Modified from Monod, 1968 and Arratia and Schultze, 1992).
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2002067|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2002068|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2002162|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:4000164|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:4000167|UBERON:0004376|UBERON:2001364

name: anal fin actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium that is part of the anal fin skeleton.

name: infraorbital
description: Dermal bone that is located anterior, ventral or posterior to the eye. Infraorbital bones may or may not contain the infraorbital sensory canal. Infraorbital bones are numbered starting with the anteriormost element of the series.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001697|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2001709|UBERON:0003462|UBERON:0008907|UBERON:0010321

name: levator arcus palatini
description: Jaw muscle that connects the sphenotic to the metapterygoid and hyomandibula and promotes the elevation/abduction of the suspensorium.

name: median tuberal portion
description: Multi-tissue structure which is part of the hypothalamus and consists of caudal and ventral zones, and is separated from the dorsal hypothalamic zone by a deep ventral sulcus. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: postcleithrum
description: Dermal bone placed postero-medially to the supracleithrum and/or cleithrum.

name: pterosphenoid
description: Endochondral bone that sutures with the orbitosphenoid anteriorly, the frontal bone dorsally and the sphenotic and prootic posteriorly. The pterosphenoid forms part of the orbitosphenoid region. The pterosphenoid bears foramina that accommodate branches of the trigeminal and facial nerves. The pterosphenoid is a paired bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002241|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003111|RO:0002131 some UBERON:0001703|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001831|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2002033|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2002217|RO:0002202 some UBERON:2001515|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0010314|UBERON:0011164

name: retroarticular
description: The retroarticular is a cartilage bone that forms at the posteroventral tip of Meckel's cartilage where the interoperculomandibular ligament attaches (5.1 mm NL). In the adult it is basically triangular in shape. The retroarticular is ligamentously connected to the interopercle and preopercle posteriorly and abuts the ventral shelf of the dentary anteriorly.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001710|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003278|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0003107|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0004768

name: opercular lateral line
description: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva positioned posteriorly to the second arch skeletal element. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.).

name: anterior lateral line nerve
description: Cranial nerve which enters the brain between cranial nerves VI and VII; contains afferents and sensory efferents to the anterior lateral line ganglia.

name: scaphium
description: Neural arch and Weberian ossicle that is reduced in size relative to other neural arches. Scaphium has a process which articulates with the first centrum.

name: caudal fin actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium that is part of the caudal fin skeleton.

name: parhypural
description: Haemal spine of last hemal arch that is pierced by the haemal canal through which the caudal vessels pass or haemal arch of preural centrum 1. Its distal part commonly supports lepidotrichia. The parhypural is an unpaired median haemal spine.

name: supraneural bone
description: Endochondral bone that is median and located in the dorsal skeletogenous septum between the cranium and the dorsal fin.

name: urohyal
description: Tendon bone that forms in the tendon of the sternohyoid muscles ventral to the anterior end of copula 1. The urohyal associates by ligaments to the ventral hypohyals or it articulates with the ventral hypohyals. The urohyal is an unpaired bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011153|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001847|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001848|RO:0002162 some (not (NCBITaxon:32523))|UBERON:0008907

name: Weberian ossicle
description: Bone that is an element associated with a Weberian vertebra.

name: otic lateral line
description: One of eight distinct lateral lines in the 4-day larva positioned anterior to the ear. A sensory system on the surface of the fish, consisting of small sensory patches (neuromasts) distributed in discrete lines over the body surface. The lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.).

name: intercalar
description: Small membrane bone homologous with a cartilage bone in more basal fishes (Patterson, 1977). Situated between the exoccipital and the pterotic at point of attachment of short ligament that originates on the ventral arm of the posttemporal.

name: branchiostegal ray
description: Dermal bone that is a flattened element that supports the branchiostegal membrane. Branchiostegal rays are generally present in a series articulating ventrally or ventro-medially with the anterior and posterior ceratobranchials whereas the most posterior ray articulates with the subopercle. The branchiostegal ray is paired.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011153|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2001875|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2002101|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:4300150|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001849|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001850|UBERON:0008907

name: caudal octavolateralis nucleus
description: Hindbrain nucleus which is part of the medulla oblongata and is a mechanoreceptive area along with the medial octavolateralis nucleus. It is smaller than the medial octavolateralis nucleus and is located lateral to the facial and vagal lobes of the medulla oblongata. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: ceratobranchial bone
description: Endochondral bone that is bilaterally paired and forms part of the ventral branchial arches.

name: infraorbital 5
description: Infraorbital that is the fifth bone of the infraorbital series.

name: dilatator operculi
description: Mandibular muscle that inserts along the dorsolateral faces of the opercles. Responsible for opercular abduction.

name: epineural
description: Some or all epineural bones ossify free from the neural arches in most teleosts. In some lower teleosts, e.g., Leptolepis, Hiodon, elopiforms and albuliforms, ossification proceeds from the attachment point of the ligament to the arch, and the epineural is a process of the neural arch. In many lower teleosts epineurals are forked proximally.

name: pelvic fin radial bone
description: Pelvic fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: intercalarium
description: Neural arch and Weberian ossicle that has been modified in shape relative to other neural arches. Intercalarium includes three parts: an anterolateral process (the manubrium) which is embedded in the interossicular ligament and the ascending and articulating processes.

name: intermuscular bone
description: Axial bone which is a segmental ossification that forms in the myoseptum.

name: pharyngobranchial bone
description: Endochondral bone of the branchial arches located medial to the epibranchials.

name: pectoral fin actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium that is part of the pectoral fin.

name: posttemporal
description: Dermal bone of the secondary pectoral girdle that attaches the girdle to the skull. Its dorsal process attaches to the epiotic or epioccipital, the ventral process to the intercalar and the body articulates with the supracleithrum. The postotic sensory canal or lateral line runs within or lateral to bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003110|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0007831|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2002059|UBERON:0007829|UBERON:0008907|UBERON:0011164

name: nucleus lateralis valvulae
description: Hindbrain nucleus in the tegmental region of rhombomere 1. The cells of the nucleus are granular and lie at the ventral border of the cerebellum and brain stem.

name: preural 1 vertebra
description: Last caudal vertebra identified as the point at which the caudal vessels bifurcate, leaving the protection of the haemal arches of the caudal vertebrae and running laterally to the hypurals. This vertebra bears, commonly, a well-developed haemal arch and its spine (parhypural).

name: posterior macula
description: Macula that is located in the developing posterior inner ear, and gives rise to the macula neglecta and the macula saccule. (See Anatomical Atlas entry for sensory patches of the ear by T. Whitfield.).

name: pterotic
description: Endochondral bone that articulates with the autosphenotic anteriorly, the parietal dorsomedially, the prootic ventrally (and the intercalar occasionally), and the epiotic and exoccipital posteriorly. The pterotic encloses the horizontal semicircular canal of the inner ear. The lower edge of the pterotic contributes to the hyomandibular facet. The pterotic is paired.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002241|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003110|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|RO:0002131 some UBERON:0001703|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001711|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0005410|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0008907|UBERON:0011164

name: kinethmoid cartilage
description: Cranial cartilage which is a small median cartilage located between the premaxillae and anterodorsal to the ethmoid.

name: preural 2 vertebra
description: Vertebra anterior to preural centrum 1; sometimes termed the 'antepenultimate' vertebra. Mabee and Bird, 2001.

name: sphenotic
description: Endochondral bone that sutures with the pterosphenoid anteriorly, the prootic ventrally, the frontal bone dorso-medially, and the pterotic dorso-posteriorly. Occasionally the sphenotic sutures with the parietal bone. The sphenotic separates the orbital from the otic region. The sphenotic bears a large antero-lateral or lateral or ventro-lateral process that borders the postero-dorsal margin of the orbit. The sphenotic is a paired bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002241|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003110|RO:0002131 some UBERON:0001703|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0006605|RO:0002202 some UBERON:2001515|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0010314|UBERON:0011164

name: supracleithrum
description: Dermal bone that articulates dorsally with the posttemporal and ventrally with the cleithrum. Supracleithrum is part of the secondary pectoral girdle and commonly, carries part of the lateral line canal.

name: pelvic fin actinotrichium
description: Actinotrichium that is part of the pelvic fin.

name: uroneural
description: Neural arch that extends along the dorso-lateral surface of the last preural centra and/or ural centra and the notochord (Arratia & Schultze, 1992). An uroneural develops as a modification of the neural arch of an ural centrum (Patterson, 1968). The series of uroneurals may include from 7 to 1 elements that are numbered from rostrad to caudad. An uroneural is a paired membrane bone.

name: valvula cerebelli
description: Brain structure which is caudally attached to the rostral medulla oblongata and extends into the tectal ventricle. The valvula cerebelli consists of a granular and a molecular layer along with aggregations of large Purkinje and eurydendroid cells and is uniquely present in ray-finned fishes. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: vertical myoseptum
description: Connective tissue partitions developing between the myotomes. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: autopalatine
description: Endochondral bone that is part of the antero-lateral region of the palate. Commonly, it articulates with the maxilla anterolaterally and with the ethmoidal region medially. It may also articulate with the dermopalatine ventro-laterally and with the entopterygoid posteriorly. The autopalatine is paired.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011085|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001608|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001784|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001942|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0004752|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0011597

name: barbel
description: Surface structure which is a tactile structure found in the branchial region. Barbels are covered with epidermis rich in taste buds, and are innervated by branches of the cranial nerves.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000033|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002199|CARO:0000000|RO:0002202 some UBERON:2005119|UBERON:3000972

name: basipterygium bone
description: Basipterygium element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: posterior ceratohyal
description: Replacement bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates anteriorly with the anterior ceratohyal.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011153|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001841|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001842|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001849|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0011610|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0010314

name: caudal motor nucleus of abducens
description: Caudal part of the abducens nucleus that mediates motor function.

name: claustrum cartilage
description: Postcranial axial cartilage and Weberian ossicle that is located dorsal to the scaphium. The claustrum cartilage is bilaterally paired.

name: commissura rostral, pars dorsalis
description: Part of the anterior commissure which is located immediately ventral to the supracommissural nucleus of area ventralis telencephali.

name: anal fin distal radial bone
description: Anal fin distal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin musculature
description: Musculature that is part of the dorsal fin.

name: rostral motor nucleus of abducens
description: Rostral part of the abducens nucleus that mediates motor function.

name: entopterygoid
description: Dermal bone that forms the ventro-medial part of the palate and the antero-ventral and ventral wall of the orbit. The entopterygoid is a paired bone.

name: epibranchial bone
description: Dorsal branchial arch bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: epural
description: A free, modified neural spine of a preural or a ural vertebra that is placed between the last developed neural spine of a preural centrum and the dorsal axis (= anterior margin of first uroneural) of the caudal skeleton . An epural commonly supports one or more dorsal procurrent rays. An epural is an unpaired median perichondrally ossified bone.

name: extrascapula
description: Dermal canal-bearing bone placed at the dorso-posterior region of the skull roof, lying on the posterior region of the pterotic and parietals, or the pterotic and epioccipital, or on the pterotic, epioccipital and occipital bones.

name: hypobranchial artery
description: A pair of HA are connect one to each AA1. They run rostromedially until at the extreme rostro-ventral midline the two vessels merge and then run straight caudally along the ventral midline until they reach the cranial end of the ventral aorta (VA). There, the single HA passes just dorsal to the rostral end of the VA and then immediately splits again into a pair of HA. The paired HA continue caudally just to either side of the ventral midline. The HA provide blood supply to the ventral branchial region and the heart.sogai et al. 2001.

name: interopercle
description: Dermal bone that is part of the opercular series. It is located ventro-medially to the preopercle and anterior to the subopercle. It is joined to the posterior part of the lower jaw (retroarticular) by a ligament. The interopercle is paired.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011152|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2000555|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2001875|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001710|UBERON:0008907

name: supraorbital bone
description: Dermal bone that is part of the dorsal or upper border or antero-dorsal border of the orbit. The supraorbital bone may contact the orbital margin of the frontal bone medially, the antorbital antero-ventrally and the dermosphenotic posteriorly. The supraorbital bone does not carry sensory canals. The supraorbital bone is paired.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001697|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2001709|UBERON:0003462|UBERON:0008907|UBERON:0010321

name: symplectic
description: Replacement bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with the hyomandibula and the quadrate.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011152|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2005268|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0011607|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0010314

name: ceratobranchial 5 tooth
description: Tooth that forms on ceratobranchial 5 cartilage or bone.

name: tripus

name: hypurapophysis
description: Lateral process, spine-like or crest-like, at the lateral wall of the haemal arch of the parhypural that serves for insertion of the hypochordal longitudinal muscle. The process may contribute to the lateral protection of the parhypural foramen (where the caudal blood vessels exit the hemal arch) and the hypural foramen (where a caudal heart may be present). The hypurapophysis is paired.

name: sclerotome somite 27
description: Ventromedial region of somite 27 that will form vertebral cartilages and connective tissues. The sclerotome lies ventral to the myotome. Cells of the sclerotome will migrate dorsally to surround the notochord and neural tube. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: sclerotome somite 3
description: Ventromedial region of somite 3 that will form vertebral cartilages and connective tissues. The sclerotome lies ventral to the myotome. Cells of the sclerotome will migrate dorsally to surround the notochord and neural tube. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: sclerotome somite 5
description: Ventromedial region of somite 5 that will form vertebral cartilages and connective tissues. The sclerotome lies ventral to the myotome. Cells of the sclerotome will migrate dorsally to surround the notochord and neural tube. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: sclerotome somite 8
description: Ventromedial region of somite 8 that will form vertebral cartilages and connective tissues. The sclerotome lies ventral to the myotome. Cells of the sclerotome will migrate dorsally to surround the notochord and neural tube. Kimmel et al, 1995.

name: primordial hindbrain channel
description: The paired vessels that run along the lateral walls of the hindbrain and drain into the anterior cardinal veins. Isogai et al. (2002).

name: lateral dorsal aorta
description: Connect the outflow of the aortic arches to the dorsal aorta. The place where the lateral dorsal aorta fuse is is called the radiax of the aorta. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: basidorsal
description: Basidorsals are bilaterally paired cartilages on the dorsolateral side of the notochord which are replaced by ossified neural arches or dorsal arcocentra. In otophysan fishes, basidorsal 1, bd2, bd3, and bd4 give rise to parts of the Weberian apparatus.

name: presumptive mesencephalic artery
description: Precursor to mesencephalic artery.

name: intestinal bulb
description: This anteriormost portion of the intestine has the most digestive enzymes and the greatest epithelial surface area. Wallace et al, 2005.

name: immature macula
description: An otic sensory epithelium that will develop into the mature macula.

name: urogenital papilla
description: A protuberance in front of the gential pore and behind the vent. Mature females have a well developed urogenital papillae whilst in mature males it is poorly developed. Brion et al, 2004.

name: organizer inducing center
description: The dorsal marginal region of the YSL where maternal dorsal determinants localize. Participates in positioning the shield. Ho et al, 1999.

name: noninvoluting endocytic marginal cell cluster
description: The NEM cell cluster lies in a superficial position of the dorsal blastoderm margin encompassing EVL cells and one or two layers of underlying deep cells. Unlike other marginal blastomeres, cells in this cluster do not participate in involution. Cooper et al, 1996.

name: ventral tooth row
description: Tooth row that is the ventralmost row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone.

name: mediodorsal tooth row
description: Tooth row that is the mediodorsal row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone, located between the dorsal tooth row and ventral tooth row.

name: dorsal tooth row
description: Tooth row that is the dorsalmost row of teeth on ceratobranchial 5 bone.

name: tooth 1V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.

name: tooth 5V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the ventral tooth row.

name: tooth 4V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 3V and anterior to tooth 5V in the ventral tooth row.

name: tooth 2V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1V and anterior to tooth 3V in the ventral tooth row.

name: tooth 3V
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2V and anterior to tooth 4V in the ventral tooth row.

name: tooth 1MD
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.

name: tooth 2MD
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 1MD and anterior to tooth 3MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.

name: tooth 1D
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the anteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.

name: tooth 2D
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the dorsal tooth row.

name: tooth 4MD
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is the posteriormost tooth in the mediodorsal tooth row.

name: tooth 3MD
description: Ceratobranchial 5 tooth which is posterior to tooth 2MD and anterior to tooth 4MD in the mediodorsal tooth row.

name: posterior lateral line primordium
description: A migrating group of cells originating from the posterior lateral line placode. The primordium deposits seven to nine neuromasts and interneuromasts between them during its posterior migration to the tail. Gompel et al, 2001.

name: vertebral element 3
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 2.

name: vertebral element 4
description: Vertebra that is anteriorly adjacent to vertebra 5.

name: os suspensorium
description: Endochondral bone and Weberian ossicle that is an element of the fourth vertebra that curves ventrally around the anterior head of the swim bladder.

name: roofing cartilage
description: Cartilaginous larval structure dorsal to the four anterior-most vertebrae, which forms the connection between neural arches and supraneurals in the Weberian apparatus. Bird and Mabee, 2003.

name: collagenous dermal stroma
description: A layer of collagen fibrils present in the imature integument in an acellular subepidermal space. At first, the fibrils are all oriented in the same direction, later they form the complex plywood-like structure that is characteristic of the dermal deep region. Le Guellec et al, 2004.

name: Weberian apparatus
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of the anteriormost vertebrae and associated structures that connect the swim bladder to the inner ear.

name: Weberian vertebra
description: Vertebra that is part of the Weberian apparatus.

name: supraneural 2 bone
description: Supraneural bone located dorsal to vertebra 2.

name: supraneural 3 bone
description: Supraneural bone that is located dorsal to vertebrae 3 and 4.

name: corpuscles of Stannius
description: Islands of eosinic cells found on the lateroventral surface of the kidney. Function is thought to be that of the parathyroid gland in other vertebrates, which are lacking in fishes. These cells secrete hypocalcin (teleocalcin) to regulate calcium metabolism.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000080|RO:0002160 some NCBITaxon:7898|RO:0002216 some GO:0055074|UBERON:0000479|UBERON:0002368|UBERON:0004120|UBERON:0005172

name: basibranchial copula
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is ventral, median, and associated with more than one pharyngeal arch in the pharyngeal arch 3-7 skeleton.

name: anterior copula
description: Copula that is ventral, median, and associated with pharyngeal arches 3-5.

name: posterior copula
description: Copula that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arches 4 and 5 (pharyngeal arches 6-7).

name: basibranchial 1 bone
description: Basibranchial bone that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 1 (pharyngeal arch 3). Typically develops in the anterior copula cartilage.

name: basibranchial 2 bone
description: Basibranchial bone that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 2 (pharyngeal arch 4). Typically develops in the anterior copula cartilage.

name: basibranchial 3 bone
description: Basibranchial bone that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 3 (pharyngeal arch 5). Typically develops in the anterior copula cartilage.

name: basibranchial 4 bone
description: Basibranchial bone that is ventral, median, and associated with branchial arch 4 (pharyngeal arch 6). Develops in posterior copula cartilage or basibranchial 4 cartilage.

name: hypobranchial 1 bone
description: Hypobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 1 element laterally. Develops in hypobranchial 1 cartilage.

name: hypobranchial 4 bone
description: Hypobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 4 element laterally. Develops in hypobranchial 4 cartilage.

name: hypobranchial 3 bone
description: Hypobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 3 element laterally. Develops in hypobranchial 3 cartilage.

name: hypobranchial 2 bone
description: Hypobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates with a median skeletal element medially and with a ceratobranchial 2 element laterally. Develops in hypobranchial 2 cartilage.

name: ceratobranchial 1 bone
description: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 1 cartilage or bone.

name: ceratobranchial 5 bone
description: Ceratobranchial bone that is the most posterior, bilaterally paired ventral pharyngeal arch bone.

name: ceratobranchial 4 bone
description: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

name: ceratobranchial 3 bone
description: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 3 cartilage or bone.

name: ceratobranchial 2 bone
description: Ceratobranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 2 cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 1 bone
description: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 1 cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 5 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and located at the articulation of epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone and the posterior tip of ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 4 bone
description: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 2 bone
description: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 2 cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 3 bone
description: Epibranchial bone that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 3 cartilage or bone and medially with pharyngobranchial cartilage or bone.
