parents: RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001861|RO:0002131 some UBERON:2001862|RO:0002202 some UBERON:2001529|UBERON:2000658|UBERON:2001907

name: pharyngobranchial 2 bone
description: Pharyngobranchial bone, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 1 element.

name: pharyngobranchial 4 cartilage
description: Most posterior pharyngobranchial cartilage, located medial to the epibranchials.

name: pharyngobranchial 3 bone
description: Pharyngobranchial bone, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 2 element.

name: medial floor plate
description: The medial portion of the spinal cord floor plate, located adjacent to the notochord.

name: ovarian follicle stage I
description: Stage I follicles (less than 140 microns) are primary growth stage. Selman et al, 1993.

name: ovarian follicle stage II
description: Stage II follicles (140-340 microns) are cortical alveolus stage. Selman et al, 1993.

name: ovarian follicle stage III
description: Stage III (340-690 microns) are vitellogenesis. Selman et al, 1993.

name: regenerating fin/limb
description: Fin or limb undergoing the process of regeneration.

name: coronomeckelian
description: Tendon bone located on the median side of the lower jaw, dorsal to Meckel's cartilage and medial to the angular. The coronomeckelian forms as an ossification of the tendon of the adductor mandibulae muscle. The coronomeckelian is a paired bone.

name: anterior chamber swim bladder
description: The anterior compartment of the swim bladder is thought to have acoustic resonance properties that play a key role in audition. It is connected to the posterior chamber via the dusctus communicans. Finney et al, 2006.

name: posterior chamber swim bladder
description: The posterior compartment of the swim bladder plays a key role in buoyancy control. It is connected to the anterior chamber via the dusctus communicans. Finney et al, 2006.

name: branchiostegal ray 1
description: Branchiostegal ray that is the anterior-most ray in the adult.

name: branchiostegal ray 3
description: Branchiostegal ray that is the third anterior-most ray in the adult.

name: branchiostegal ray 2
description: Branchiostegal ray that is the second anterior-most ray in the adult.

name: posterior lateral line ganglion
description: The posterior lateral line ganglion develops from a cranial ectodermal placode and contains sensory neurons that innervate the posterior lateral line system.

name: anterior lateral line placode
description: Dorsolateral placode that gives rise to the anterior lateral line.

name: supradorsal
description: Supradorsals are small paired nodules of cartilage positioned at the distal ends of neural arches and the proximal end of neural spines (Arratia et al., 2001).

name: nucleus of the tract of the postoptic commissure
description: The nucleus containing the cell bodies of neurons whose axons form the postoptic commissure.

name: intervening zone
description: A zone of delayed differentiation at the midbrainhindbrain boundary. The IZ separates midbrain from anterior hindbrain neuronal clusters and has been described in all vertebrates. Geling et al, 2003.

name: basiventral
description: Basiventrals are bilaterally paired cartilages lateral to the notochord which are replaced by ossified parapophyses or hemal arches.

name: neural complex of Weberian apparatus
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of supraneural 2 bone and supraneural 3 bone and their extensions, and which is part of the Weberian apparatus.

name: hemal spine
description: Hemal spines are extensions of hemal arches in the ventral skeletogenous septum of the caudal region.

name: epibranchial bone uncinate process
description: Epibranchials 1-3 in adults are compound elements formed by the fusion of epibranchial cartilages and the so-called uncinate processes. Posteromedially directed uncinate processes develop on the posterior edge of epibranchials 1-3. These appear as separate centers of chondrification (6.2 mm) that later fuse laterally to the posterior edges of the epibranchial cartilages (6.8 mm).

name: epithelial mesenchymal boundary of regenerating fin/limb
description: An epithelial-mesenchymal boundary that is part of a regenerating fin/limb.

name: regeneration epithelium of fin/limb
description: An epithelium that is part of a regenerating fin/limb.

name: anterior lateral line ganglion
description: The anteror lateral line ganglia develops from cranial ectodermal placodes and contain sensory neurons that innervate the anterior lateral line system.

name: parapophysis 1
description: Parapophysis that is the lateral projections from the first centrum in cyprinids, absent in catostomids, and absent in characiphysans (Fink and Fink, 1996).

name: parapophysis 2
description: Parapophysis that is lateral projection from the second centrum, absent in Siluriformes (Fink and Fink, 1996).

name: neural arch 3
description: Neural arch 3 is expanded and fused to supraneural 3 as part of a neural complex roofing and protecting the neural canal.

name: neural arch 4
description: Neural arch 4 is expanded and fused to supraneural 3 as part of the neural complex. A reduced neural spine projects from the posterior margin of the neural complex.

name: parapophysis + rib of vertebra 4
description: The parapophysis + rib, fused to the centrum, extends laterally then angles anteroventrally. A thin plate, the os suspensorium fuses to its median surface.

name: post-Weberian supraneural
description: Posterior to the Weberian apparatus, otophysan supraneurals form as median, unpaired, rod- or platelike elements, as in other actinopterygians.

name: supraethmoid
description: Dermal bone that first appears as paired ossifications in the membrane (dermis) dorsolateral to the ethmoid cartilage and anterolateral to the lateral ethmoids, later having the appearance of one butterfly-shaped element. Fused to the anterodorsal margin of the mesethmoid. Bordered anteriorly by the kinethmoid and posteriorly by the frontal.

name: preethmoid bone
description: Small rounded to egg-shaped cartilage bone that sits in an anterolateral depression on the prevomer. Articulates with the autopalatine in all cypriniforms.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002241|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003112|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0011242|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0010314|UBERON:0011164

name: kinethmoid bone
description: Sesamoid bone located in the premaxillary-ethmoid ligament, between the mesethmoid and the premaxilla. The kinethmoid is an unpaired median bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001709|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002241|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003112|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0008907|UBERON:0011164|UBERON:0011597

name: infraorbital 2
description: Infraorbital that is the second bone of the infraorbital series.

name: infraorbital 3
description: Infraorbital that is the third bone of the infraorbital series.

name: infraorbital 4
description: Infraorbital that is the fourth bone of the infraorbital series.

name: epiotic
description: Endochondral bone that borders that medial edge of the posttemporal fossa. The epiotics are sutured to parietals and supraoccipital dorsally, the exoccipitals ventrally and the pterotics laterally. The epiotic is a paired bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002241|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003110|RO:0002131 some UBERON:0001703|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0005410|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0004121|UBERON:0010314|UBERON:0011164

name: pelvic fin distal radial bone 2
description: Pelvic fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pelvic fin distal radial bone 3
description: Pelvic fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pelvic fin distal radial bone 1
description: Pelvic fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin pterygiophore
description: A range of seven to nine rod-like internal median skeletal support structures of the dorsal fin, comprised of both bone and cartilage and found between vertebrae 11 and 18.

name: anal fin pterygiophore
description: A range of twelve to fourteen rod-like internal median skeletal support structures of the anal fin, comprised of both bone and cartilage and found between vertebrae 14 and 21.

name: pneumatic duct
description: A duct connecting the esophagus to the posterior chamber of the swim bladder. Finney et al, 2006.

name: anterior sclerotic bone
description: Sclerotic bone that is located anterior to the eye.

name: posterior sclerotic bone
description: Sclerotic bone that is located posterior to the eye.

name: ductus communicans
description: The constriction between the anterior and posterior chambers of the swim bladder. There does not appear to be an identifiable sphincter in the ductus, and therefore other musculature may regulate its opening. Finney et al, 2006.

name: apical ectodermal ridge pelvic fin
description: Apical ectodermal ridge that is part of the pelvic fin.

name: pectoral fin endoskeletal disc
description: A plate-like chondrogenic condensation within the pectoral fin, which subdivides into individual radials by decomposition of extracellular matrix in the inter-radial mesenchyme (Grandel and Schulte-Merker, 1998).

name: postcranial axial cartilage
description: Cartilage which is part of the axial skeleton.

name: anterior lateral line system
description: The anterior lateral line system develops from cranial ectodermal placodes, situated between the eye and the ear, that give rise to both the neuromasts and the anterior lateral line sensory nerves that innervate the neuromasts. The anterior lateral line system consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head of all fishes and most amphibians and are innervated by several lateral line nerves, which project to the hindbrain. The anterior lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance.

name: anterior lateral line
description: The anterior lateral line consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head of all fishes and most amphibians. The anterior lateral line develops from cranial ectodermal placodes situated between the eye and ear.

name: posterior lateral line system
description: The posterior lateral line system develops from cranial ectodermal placodes, situated behind the ear, that give rise to both the neuromasts and the posterior lateral line sensory nerves that innervate the neuromasts. The posterior lateral line system consists of small sensory patches (neuromasts) located superficially on the skin or just under the skin in fluid-filled canals on the head of all fishes and most amphibians. The neuromasts are innervated by several lateral line nerves, which project primarily to the hindbrain. The posterior mechanosensory lateral line system is stimulated by local water displacements and vibrations, and detects propulsion of the fish through the water, as well as facilitating shoaling, prey capture, and predator and obstacle avoidance.

name: anterior lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the anterior lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.).

name: dorsal anterior lateral line nerve
description: Nerve fibers originating from the dorsal anterior lateral line ganglion. These rami innervate the otic, supraorbital, and infraorbital neuromasts.

name: ventral anterior lateral line nerve
description: Nerve fibers originating from the ventral anterior lateral line ganglion. These rami innervate the mandibular and opercular neuromasts.

name: middle lateral line nerve
description: Nerve fibers originating from the middle lateral line ganglion. These fibers innervate the middle lateral line.

name: middle lateral line ganglion
description: The middle lateral line ganglion develops from a cranial ectodermal placode and contains sensory neurons that innervate the middle lateral line.

name: epiphyseal bar
description: Bilaterally paired medial bar of cartilage formed at midorbit through medial chondrification from triangles of cartilage that later form the junction of the taeniae marginales anterior, taeniae marginales posterior and the epiphyseal bar.

name: occipital arch cartilage
description: Cranial cartilage which is a paired anterodorsal projection of the posterior end of the parachordal cartilage. It lies lateral to the notochord, just anterior to the posterior tip of the otic capsule. The bilaterally paired occipital arch cartilages fuse anterodorsally to the posterior edges of the auditory capsules and meet medially as the tectum synoticum (by 12 dpf).

name: taenia marginalis anterior
description: Cartilage bar (bilaterally paired) that grows anteroventrally from the epiphyseal bar to join the anterolatera1 edge of the ethmoid plate.

name: trabecula communis
description: Cartilage formed via medial fusion between bilaterally paired trabecula crani.

name: interhyal cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates dorsally with the hyosymplectic cartilage or the articulation of the hyomandibula and symplectic.

name: taenia marginalis posterior
description: Cartilage bar (bilaterally paired) that is first visible as an anterior extension of the auditory capsule. It grows anteriorly toward the middle of the orbit where it is connected to its mate on the other side by the epiphyseal bar.

name: ceratobranchial cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that forms the largest skeletal element of the ventral branchial arches.

name: ceratobranchial 2 cartilage
description: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 2 cartilage or bone.

name: ceratobranchial 3 cartilage
description: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 3 cartilage or bone.

name: ceratobranchial 4 cartilage
description: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

name: ceratobranchial 1 cartilage
description: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with epibranchial 1 cartilage or bone.

name: ceratobranchial 5 cartilage
description: Ceratobranchial cartilage that is the most posterior, bilaterally paired ventral pharyngeal arch cartilage.

name: hypobranchial cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates medially with a median skeletal element and laterally with a ceratobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: hypobranchial 4 cartilage
description: Hypobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

name: hypobranchial 1 cartilage
description: Hypobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 1 cartilage or bone.

name: hypobranchial 2 cartilage
description: Hypobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 2 cartilage or bone.

name: hypobranchial 3 cartilage
description: Hypobranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 3 cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial cartilage
description: Pharyngeal arch cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 1 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 1 cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 3 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 3 cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 2 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 2 cartilage or bone.

name: epibranchial 4 cartilage
description: Epibranchial cartilage that is bilaterally paired and articulates laterally with ceratobranchial 4 cartilage or bone.

name: pharyngobranchial cartilage
description: Paired cartilages that project medially from the medial tips of epibranchials.

name: pharyngobranchial 3 cartilage
description: Pharyngobranchial cartilage, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 2 element.

name: pharyngobranchial 2 cartilage
description: Pharyngobranchial cartilage, located medial to the epibranchials and posteriorly adjacent to pharyngobranchial 1 element.

name: mesocoracoid cartilage
description: Pectoral fin cartilage that is part of the embryonic primary pectoral girdle from which the mesocoracoid bone will ossify endochondrally.

name: pelvic radial cartilage
description: Small cartilage that forms at the posterior edge of the basipterygium.

name: basipterygium cartilage
description: Bilaterally paired small, rodlike cartilages on the ventral surface of the abdomen (present at 7.9 mm). Their posterior tips expand laterally, forming L-shaped cartilages. Medially, a posterior spur of cartilage develops, which will later ossify as the ischiac process (Weitzman 1962).

name: pelvic radial 3 cartilage
description: Small cartilage that forms at the posterior and medial edge of the basipterygium.

name: pelvic radial 2 cartilage
description: Small cartilage with a long posterior process and a shorter lateral one that forms at the posterior edge of the basipterygium, between radial cartilages 1 and 2.

name: pelvic radial 1 cartilage
description: Small cartilage that forms at the posterior and lateral edge of the basipterygium.

name: neural spine 4
description: Neural spine that is associated with the fourth vertebra.

name: premaxilla ascending process
description: Process of the premaxilla that extends posteriorly and overlays the mesethmoid.

name: anterior dorsomedial process of autopalatine
description: In cypriniforms the anterior portion of the palatine has a dorsomedial process which abuts against the mesethmoid. Such a process is not present in other ostariophysans or in other primitive teleosts.

name: ural vertebra 2
description: Ural vertebra that is the second vertebra posterior to preural centrum 1. It may bear a rudimentary neural arch and sometimes a rudimentary spine or the neural arch and spine are completely absent and it may articulate or fuse with hypural 2 (polyural terminology). Ural vertebra 2 is an unpaired median bone.

name: ural centrum 2
description: A vertebral centrum that is located immediately posterior to ural centrum 1. Ural centrum 2 is an unpaired median bone.

name: preural centrum 1+ ural centrum 1
description: Urostyle that is the result of fusion of preural centrum 1 with the first ural centrum (of polyural terminology).

name: caudal procurrent ray
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that form part of the anterior dorsal and ventral series of lepidotrichia of the caudal fin that may be associated with a neural spine or an epural or an uroneural (dorsal series) and with a haemal spine of a preural vertebra (ventral series). Caudal procurrent rays are shorter than the caudal principal rays. A caudal procurrent ray is an unpaired median bone.

name: caudal principal ray
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that is adjacent to a branched ray. Caudal principal rays may be segmented but unbranched and the main element forming the dorsal or ventral leading margin of the caudal fin or a ray that may be only segmented-and-branched and forms part of the middle-posterior region of the fin. A caudal principal ray is an unpaired median bone.

name: pectoral fin radial bone
description: Pectoral fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pectoral fin proximal radial bone
description: Pectoral fin proximal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pectoral fin distal radial bone
description: Pectoral fin distal radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: propterygium cartilage
description: The propterygium is the lateralmost or anteriormost basal cartilage that originates from the pectoral fin endoskeletal disc. The bases of the pectoral lepidotrichium 1 plus the propterygium articulates with the scapula.

name: claustrum bone
description: Endochondral bone, membrane bone, and Weberian ossicle that is located dorsal to the scaphium. The claustrum bone is bilaterally paired.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2001871|RO:0000056 some GO:0036072|RO:0002202 some UBERON:2000637|RO:0002473 some UBERON:0002481|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:4300190

name: caudal fin upper lobe
description: Surface structure that is the dorsal portion of the caudal fin.

name: caudal fin lower lobe
description: Surface structure that is the ventral portion of the caudal fin.

name: autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the autopalatine and lateral ethmoid and bones. Autopalatine-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.

name: sensory canal
description: Multi-tissue structure that is a fluid-filled canal in the integument and usually dermal bones, and contains one or more neuromast organs.

name: trunk sensory canal
description: Sensory canal on trunk which is posterior to the pectoral girdle and often reaching to or onto the caudal fin. The trunk sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

name: post-otic sensory canal
description: Sensory canal between and in close proximity to the trunk sensory canal and anteriorly with the otic and preoperculo-mandibular sensory canals. The post-otic sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

name: lagenar capsule
description: Anatomical cluster that consists of a bulla formed by the exoccipital and basioccipital bones, and surrounds the lagena.

name: otic sensory canal
description: Sensory canal between and in close proximity posteriorly with the post-otic and preoperculo-mandibular sensory canals, and anteriorly with the supraorbital and infraorbital sensory canals. The otic sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

name: supratemporal sensory canal
description: Sensory canal that crosses over the dorsal midline and in close proximity to the contralateral post-otic sensory canals. The supratemporal sensory canal is unpaired.

name: notochordal ossification
description: Perichordal bone that surrounds the anterior tip of the notochord.

name: rudimentary neural arch
description: Neural arch on the urostyle. It does not support a neural spine. Sanger and McCune 2002.

name: anal fin radial bone
description: Anal fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin radial bone
description: Dorsal fin radial element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: mesethmoid-lateral ethmoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and lateral ethmoid. Mesethmoid-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.

name: mesethmoid-vomer joint
description: Joint that articulates the mesethmoid and vomer. Mesethmoid-vomer joint is unpaired.

name: lateral ethmoid-ectopterygoid ligament
description: Lateral ethmoid-ectopterygoid ligament is a ligament that connects the lateral ethmoid to the ectopterygoid.

name: bony shelf above orbit
description: The bony shelf above orbit is an anatomical cluster formed by the dorsolateral portions of the lateral ethmoid, frontal and sphenotic bones that forms the dorsal margin of the orbit.

name: interopercular-mandibular ligament
description: Interopercular-mandibular ligament is a ligament that connects the interopercle to an element of the lower jaw, typically the retroarticular.

name: infraorbital series
description: Anatomical cluster that is the series of dermal bones surrounding the orbit and associated with the infraorbital sensory canal.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003113|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0011156|CARO:0000000|RO:0002473 some UBERON:2000376|UBERON:0000477

name: opercle-interopercle joint
description: Joint that articulates the opercle and interopercle. Opercle-interopercle joint is paired.

name: frontal-pterotic joint
description: Joint that articulates the frontal and pterotic. Frontal-pterotic joint is paired.

name: caudal principal ray 1
description: Caudal principal ray that is the dorsalmost caudal principal ray of the caudal fin.

name: caudal principal ray 2
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 1.

name: caudal principal ray 3
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 2.

name: caudal principal ray 4
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 3.

name: caudal principal ray 5
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 4.

name: caudal principal ray 6
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 5.

name: caudal principal ray 7
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 6.

name: caudal principal ray 8
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 7.

name: caudal principal ray 9
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 8.

name: caudal principal ray 10
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 9.

name: caudal principal ray 11
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 10.

name: caudal principal ray 12
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 11.

name: caudal principal ray 13
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 12.

name: caudal principal ray 14
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 13.

name: caudal principal ray 15
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 14.

name: caudal principal ray 16
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 15.

name: caudal principal ray 17
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 16.

name: caudal principal ray 18
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 17.

name: caudal principal ray 19
description: Caudal principal ray that is ventrally adjacent to caudal principal ray 18.

name: vertebral element 5
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 4.

name: scapular foramen
description: Foramen that is located in the scapula. The scapular foramen is paired and formed by a ring of bone.

name: coracoid foramen
description: Foramen that is located in the coracoid.

name: auditory foramen
description: Foramen through which cranial nerve VIII (auditory) exits.

name: superficial ophthalmic nerve foramen
description: Foramen through which the superficial ophthalmic nerve passes.

name: dentary-anguloarticular joint
description: Joint that articulates the dentary and anguloarticular. Dentary-anguloarticular joint is paired.

name: rib of vertebra 6
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the sixth centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 5
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the fifth centrum.

name: posttemporal fossa
description: Fossa where the exoccipital forms the medial portion and the epioccipital forms the lateral margin. The posttemporal fossa in most species has two openings separated by the epioccipital bridge.

name: pectoral fin ray 1
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium 1 is the leading or marginal ray of the fin and articulates with the scapula. Lepidotrichium 1 is commonly segmented but unbranched but occasionally may be a massive strong unsegmented element (e.g., spine).

name: pectoral fin ray 2
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the second most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 3
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the third most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 4
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the fourth most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 5
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the fifth most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 6
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the sixth most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: pectoral fin ray 7
description: Pectoral fin lepidotrichium that, in a linear sequence, is the seventh most anterior pectoral ray that it is usually branched and segmented.

name: autopalatine-vomer joint
description: Joint that articulates autopalatine and vomer bones. Autopalatine-vomer joint is paired.

name: orbitosphenoid-prootic joint
description: Joint that articulates orbitosphenoid and prootic bones. Orbitosphenoid-prootic joint is paired.

name: recessus lateralis
description: Intracranial space formed by confluence of supraorbital, infraorbital, preopercular and temporal sensory canals. See also Di Dario (2004).

name: quadrate-hyomandibula joint
description: Joint that articulates quadrate and hyomandibula bones. Quadrate-hyomandibula joint is paired.

name: quadrate-metapterygoid joint
description: Joint that articulates quadrate and metapterygoid bones. Quadrate-metapterygoid joint is paired.

name: olfactory nerve foramen
description: Foramen for the passage of the olfactory nerve or cranial nerve 1.

name: articular bone
description: Endochondral bone that is located posterior to the dentary, medial to the angular and antero-dorsal to the retroarticular forming the lower jaw. The articular bears a dorso-posterior articular facet for the condyle of the quadrate. The articular is a paired bone.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0001710|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0003278|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0003107|UBERON:0002513|UBERON:0004768

name: supraorbital sensory canal
description: Sensory canal anterior to and in close proximity to the otic and infraorbital sensory canals. The supraorbital sensory canal is bilaterally paired.

name: infraorbital sensory canal
description: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity to the otic and supraorbital sensory canals at their union. The infraorbital sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the infraorbital bones.

name: preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity to the otic and post-otic sensory canals at their union. The preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the preopercle, angular and dentary bones.

name: preopercular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal lateral or ventral to and in close proximity with the otic and post-otic sensory canals at their union, and anteroventrally with the mandibular sensory canal. The preopercular sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the preopercle bone.

name: mandibular sensory canal
description: Sensory canal anterior and ventral to and in close proximity with the preoperculo-mandibular sensory canal. The mandible sensory canal is bilaterally paired and associated with the angular and dentary bones.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 1
description: Dorsal fin proximal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 2
description: Dorsal fin proximal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: notochord posterior region
description: Portion of tissue that is part of the caudal fin.

name: lateral line scale
description: Scale that is associated with the lateral line sensory canal.

name: premaxillary-maxillary ligament
description: Ligament that connects the premaxilla to the maxilla.

name: primordial ligament
description: Ligament that connects the maxilla with the lower jaw.

name: caudal fin dorsal procurrent ray
description: Caudal procurrent ray that forms part of the anterior dorsal series of lepidotrichia of the caudal fin and may be associated with a neural spine or a epural or a uroneural. A pair of hemitrichia forms each ray.

name: caudal fin ventral procurrent ray
description: Caudal procurrent ray that forms part of the anterior ventral series of lepidotrichia of the caudal fin that may be associated with a neural spine or a epural or an uroneural (dorsal series) and with a hemal spine of a preural vertebra (ventral series). A caudal procurrent ray is an unpaired median bone.

name: pterosphenoid-orbitosphenoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the pterosphenoid and orbitosphenoid. Pterosphenoid-orbitosphenoid joint is paired.

name: parasphenoid-basioccipital joint
description: Joint that articulates the parasphenoid and basioccipital. Parasphenoid-basioccipital joint is unpaired.

name: interhyal-epihyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the interhyal and epihyal bones, or interhyal and ceratohyal cartilages. Interhyal-epihyal joint is paired.

name: epihyal-ceratohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the epihyal and ceratohyal bones. Epihyal-ceratohyal joint is paired.

name: ceratohyal-dorsal hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and dorsal hypohyal bones. Ceratohyal-dorsal hypohyal joint is paired.

name: ceratohyal-ventral hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and ventral hypohyal bones. Ceratohyal-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

name: dorsal hypohyal-ventral hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the dorsal hypohyal and ventral hypohyal bones. Dorsal hypohyal-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

name: inter-ventral hypohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the contralateral ventral hypohyal bones or the contralateral ceratobranchial cartilages. Inter-ventral hypohyal joint is paired.

name: dorsal hypohyal-urohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the dorsal hypohyal and urohyal bones. Dorsal hypohyal-urohyal joint is paired.
parents: RO:0002176 some UBERON:0011610|RO:0002176 some UBERON:2000196|RO:0002176 some UBERON:2000452|UBERON:0000982

name: ventral hypohyal-urohyal joint
description: Joint that articulates the ventral hypohyal and urohyal bones. Ventral hypohyal-urohyal joint is paired.

name: epihyal-branchiostegal ray joint
description: Joint that articulates the epihyal and branchiostegal ray bones. Epihyal-branchiostegal ray joint is paired.

name: ceratohyal-branchiostegal ray joint
description: Joint that articulates the ceratohyal and branchiostegal ray bones. Ceratohyal-branchiostegal ray joint is paired.

name: gill ray
description: Gill ray is a slender, usually rod-like cartilage within a gill filament and ligamentously tied to its associated pharyngeal arch bone or cartilage.

name: inter-hypobranchial 3 joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right hypobranchial 3 cartilages or bones. Inter-hypobranchial 3 joint is unpaired.

name: head sensory canal system
description: Lateral line system on head and pectoral girdle.

name: rib of vertebra 2
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the second centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 1
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the first centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 3
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the third centrum.

name: rib of vertebra 4
description: Rib that articulates with the parapophysis of the fourth centrum.

name: inter-frontal joint
description: Joint between the left and right frontal bone.

name: anterior myodome
description: Fossa or chamber on anterior portion of orbital region of neurocranium that serves as attachment site for anterior extrinsic eye musculature.

name: articular fossa of opercle
description: Fossa of opercle that articulates with hyomandibular condyle for opercle.

name: sensory canal tubular ossicle
description: Dermal bone that is ring-shaped or cylindrical and surrounds a sensory canal.

name: sensory canal tubule
description: Sensory canal that is a side branch between a sensory canal proximally and a pore at its distal end. Sensory canal tubule is bilaterally paired although often imperfectly so.

name: anterior nasal barbel
description: Barbel that is associated with the anterior nostril. Anterior nasal barbel is paired.

name: maxillary barbel
description: Barbel that is attached to the distal end of the maxilla and that originates on the side of the mouth. Maxillary barbel is paired.

name: inter-basipterygium joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right basipterygium cartilage or bone. Inter-basipterygium joint is unpaired.

name: vertebra 4-vertebra 5 joint
description: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses of vertebra 4 and vertebra 5.

name: orbitosphenoid-lateral ethmoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the orbitosphenoid cartilage or bone and lateral ethmoid cartilage or bone. Orbitosphenoid-lateral ethmoid joint is paired.

name: autopalatine-maxillary joint
description: Joint that articulates the autopalatine cartilage or bone and maxilla.

name: lateral ethmoid-autopalatine ligament
description: Lateral ethmoid-autopalatine ligament is a ligament that connects the lateral ethmoid to the autopalatine.

name: hyomandibular-otic region joint
description: Joint that articulates the hyomandibular cartilage or bone and otic region cartilage or sphenotic bone, and often pterotic bone and prootic bone. Hyomandibular-otic region joint is paired.

name: inter-premaxillary joint
description: Joint that articulates the left and right premaxillary bones. Inter-premaxillary joint is unpaired.

name: skin flap
description: Surface structure that is a portion of skin that projects or hangs from the body.

name: inner mental barbel
description: Mental barbel that originates on the chin, in an anteromedial position relative to the outer mental barbel. The inner mental barbel is nearer to the mandibular symphysis than is the outer mental barbel.

name: intercostal ligament
description: Ligament that connects one rib to another.

name: hyomandibula-metapterygoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the hyomandibula bone and metapterygoid bone.

name: vertebral element 6
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 5.

name: vertebral element 7
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 6.

name: vertebral element 8
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 7.

name: branched anal fin ray
description: Anal fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched.

name: hyoideomandibular nerve
description: Nerve that is a branch of cranial nerve VII that passes through or around the suspensorium to innervate muscles and sensory organs on or near pharyngeal arch 2.

name: lateral fontanel of frontal
description: Fontanel within the frontal bone near the frontal-sphenotic joint. Lateral fontanel of frontal is paired.

name: dentary foramen
description: Foramen located on the dentary for passage of the mandibular nerve.

name: mental barbel
description: Barbel that originates on the chin.

name: orbital foramen
description: Foramen in the bone or cartilage comprising the anterior wall of the orbit, and through which passes at least the deep ophthalmic branch of cranial nerve V (trigeminal).

name: lateral ethmoid-frontal joint
description: Joint that articulates the lateral ethmoid and frontal. lateral ethmoid-frontal joint is paired.

name: prootic-pterosphenoid joint
description: Joint that articulates the prootic and pterosphenoid. prootic-pterosphenoid joint is paired.

name: prootic-exoccipital joint
description: Joint that articulates the prootic and exoccipital. Prootic-exoccipital joint is paired.

name: basioccipital-exoccipital joint
description: Joint that articulates the basioccipital and exoccipital. Basioccipital-exoccipital joint is paired.

name: inter-coracoid joint
description: Joint between the right and left coracoid bones of the pectoral girdle.

name: scale circulus
description: Fine ridge on surface of scale, often parallel to the circumference of scale.

name: prootic depression
description: Shallow area that exists on the prootic.

name: bony plate
description: Dermal bone that is located on or subjacent to the surface anywhere on the body and that is not part of the general complement of scales, dermal bone of the dermatocranium, postcranial axial skeleton or paired fin skeleton. Bony plate may exist singly, or as unpaired or paired clusters or series.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002090|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002199|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:2002096|UBERON:0008907

name: vertebra 5-vertebra 6 joint
description: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses.

name: vertebra 6 - vertebra 7 joint
description: Joint between the centra, and sometimes the neural arches or parapophyses of vertebra 6 and vertebra 7.

name: gill opening
description: Anatomical space that is the external opening of a gill slit connecting the pharyngeal cavity to the exterior. Gill opening is usually paired and located on the lateral or ventral surfaces of the head.

name: branched caudal fin ray
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium that is distally branched.

name: auditory fenestra
description: Opening in the neurocranium to allow communication between the swimbladder and the inner ear.

name: dorsal fin pterygiophore 1
description: Dorsal fin pterygiophore that is the anteriormost pterygiophore of the dorsal fin.

name: annular ligament
description: Ligament that is in the eye and is located at the angle between the cornea and the iris.

name: anterior swim bladder bud
description: Portion of tissue that forms from the swim bladder epithelium at the anterior end of the swim bladder.

name: vertebral element 9
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 8.

name: vertebral element 10
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 9.

name: vertebral element 11
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 10.

name: vertebral element 12
description: Vertebra that is posteriorly adjacent to vertebra 11. May have hemal arch and rib.

name: opercular cavity
description: Anatomical space which is located beneath the operculum and external to the gills.

name: octaval nerve motor nucleus
description: Hindbrain nucleus which consists of cell bodies whose axons exit the hindbrain via cranial nerve VIII and innervate hair cells of the lateral line and inner ear. The neurons of these nuclei are unusual in that they extend both contra- and ipsilateral dendrites.

name: climbing fiber
description: Portion of tissue that consists of afferent axons from the inferior olive and synapsing with Purkinje cells within the molecular layer of the valvula cerebelli and corpus cerebelli.

name: dorsolateral motor nucleus of vagal nerve
description: Motor nucleus of vagal nerve that is located within the dorsolateral portion of rhomobomere 8.

name: dorsolateral septum
description: Portion of tissue that grows in from the dorsolateral wall of the otic vesicle, forming a dorsolateral partition between the developing anterior and posterior semicircular canals.

name: epidermal placode
description: Portion of tissue that is a thickening and reshaping of the epidermal basal stratum cells beneath which fibroblasts accumulate to form the scale primordium.

name: hypobranchial muscle
description: Head muscle that originates on the anterior region of the cleithrum and inserts on the urohyal. The hypobranchial forms initially as left and right parts that later fuse together forming a cone shape.

name: intermediate nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus which is located between the dorsal hypothalamus and the caudal tuberal nucleus and does not contain tyrosine hydroxylase immunoreactive cells.

name: preglomerular nucleus
description: Diencephalic nucleus which is located in the caudal tuberculum. The preglomerular nuclei make up most of the migrated nuclei within the caudal tuberculum. From Neuroanatomy of the Zebrafish Brain.

name: mid cerebral vein
description: The mesencephalic veins (MsV) enter the mid cerebral veins (MCeV) at the dorsal midline. THe MCeVs originate at the dorsal midline, proceede lateraly in a ventral direction to drain into the paired primordial midbrain channels (PHBC). ogai et al. 2001., Kimmel et al. 1993.

name: pseudobranchial artery
description: A vascular loop attached to the efferent part of the mandibular arch that forms at 3.5 dpf. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: concurrent branch afferent branchial artery
description: The branch of the afferent branchial artery that continues posteriodorsally. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: recurrent branch afferent branchial artery
description: The anterioventral proceeding branch of the afferent branchial artery. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: primordial midbrain channel
description: The vessel between the anterior cerebral vein and the mid cerebral vein. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: central artery
description: Arteries that irrigate the forebrain and midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: cerebellar central artery
description: Extend upward from the PCS, branch to provide an arterial feed to the hindbrain, then drain back down into the PHBC Isogai et al. 2001.

name: opercular artery
description: The opercular artery arises from the hyoid stump on the first aortic arch, then follows the lateral margin of the operculum (gill covering) ventrally to reconnect into the proximal part of the first aortic arch. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: dorsal longitudinal anastomotic vessel
description: Trunk vessel that connects to the primitive hindbrain channel and the basilar artery at the caudal end of the medulla oblongata. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: primary head sinus
description: Main route for venous drainage of the anterior and mid cerebral veins as well as portions of the primordial hindbrain channel. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: posterior cerebral vein
description: Vein that drains the dorsal longitudinal vessel and the caudal portions of the venous capillary network of the medulla oblongata. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: rostral blood island
description: Hematopoietic tissue derived from the cephalic mesoderm. Predominantly produces myeloid cells. de Jong and Zon 2005.

name: dorsal longitudinal vein
description: Vessel that connects to the primitive hindbrain channel and the basilar artery at the caudal end of the medulla oblongata. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: optic vein
description: Vein that connects to the hyaloid vein that drains the eye. External to eye. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: parachordal vessel
description: Vessels run longitudinally along the horizontal myoseptum. These vessels are not functional until after lumenization which occurs near 4 dpf. Isogai et al. 2003.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002201|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0010204|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0002065|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0007679|UBERON:0003481|UBERON:0003513

name: supraintestinal artery
description: A continuation of the anterior mesenteric artery, which branches out from the dorsal aorta just caudal to the pronephric glomus. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: optic artery
description: The artery that carries blood to the eye. It branches from the internal carotid artery and enters the eye ventrally through the optic fissure. Isogai et al. 2001.
parents: BFO:0000050 some RO:0002577|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002200|RO:0002178 some UBERON:0000019|UBERON:0001637|UBERON:0003496

name: primitive prosencephalic artery
description: Vessel that branches from cranial division of the internal carotid artery, extending laterally around the rostral end of the head. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: prosencephalic artery
description: After the primitive prosencephalic artery forms it becomes disconnected from the cranial division of the internal carotid artery and instead it connects to the anterior mesencephalic central artery and the communicating vessels of the palatocerebral artery.

name: palatocerebral artery
description: The PLA branches ventrally from the CrDI. It extends rostrally along the base of mid- and forebrain, then loops medially and links to the corresponding vessel from the other side of the embryo. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: communicating vessel palatocerebral artery
description: Connect the palatocerebral artery with the prosencephalic artery. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: anterior mesencephalic central artery
description: Arteries that irrigate rostral regions of the midbrain. They extend between the Basial communicating artery to the anterior cerebral vein. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: median palatocerebral vein
description: Drains the PLA loop proceeds straight caudally along the cranial midline just above the pharynx, just below the diencephalon. Forms a 'T' with the palatocerebral veins. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: palatocerebral vein
description: Vein that drains the median palatocerebral vein into the optic vein. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: bulbus arteriosus outer layer
description: Composed of scattered layers of interrupted elastic lamina. Hu et al. 2001.

name: bulbus arteriosus middle layer
description: Composed of 7-10 layers of helically arranged smooth muscle cells surrounded by a fine network of collagen, reticular, and elastic fibrils. Hu et al. 2001.

name: bulbus arteriosus inner layer
description: Composed of subendothelium with longitudinally oriented collagen, reticular fibrils, elastic fibers, and smooth muscle cells bound by a thin endothelial layer. Hu et al. 2001.

name: central cardiac conduction system
description: Cardiac conduction system, characterized by slow impulse propagation and prolonged refractory periods.

name: peripheral cardiac conduction system
description: Portion of the cardiac conduction system, with rapid impulse propagation.

name: middle mesencephalic central artery
description: Project rostrally and dorsally from the AMCtA to to irrigate the midportion of the midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: posterior mesencephalic central artery
description: Project dorsally from BCA to irrigate the caudal part of midbrain Isogai et al. 2001.

name: anterior mesenteric artery
description: Unpaired artery departing from dorsal aorta, typically supplying the small intestine.

name: metencephalic artery
description: These arteies branch dorsally from both sides of the posterior communicating artery looping up to join with the opposite MtA as well as with both middle cerebral veins at the dorsal midline of the head. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: nasal artery
description: The nasal arteries start at the internal carotid artey and travel rostrally, passing along the right and left walls of the nasal sac at the most rostral end of the head. From the nasal sac, the NA flows into the nasal veins. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: posterior mesenteric artery
description: Unpaired artery departing from dorsal aorta that typically supplies the large intestine.

name: swim bladder artery
description: An elaborate set of vessels that branche off caudally from the anterior mesenteric artery just after the dorsal aorta. The SBA vascular loops are located on the ventral side of the swim bladder. Isogai et al. 2001.

name: central ray artery
description: Positioned in the intraray mesenchym between the hemirays of the lepidotrichia,. Huang et al. 2003.

name: ray vein
description: Lie flanking and just lateral to the fin ray, in the interray mesenchyme. Huang et al. 2003.

name: intervessel commissure
description: Vessels that travel between artery and veins or vein and vein in a single ray.

name: interray vessel
description: Vessels that travel between veins in adjacent rays.

name: dorsal lateral line neuromast
description: Neuromast that is part of the dorsal lateral line. Kimmel et al, 1995. (Also see Anatomical Atlas entry for lateral line by T. Whitfield.).

name: primary posterior lateral line primordium
description: Primordium that forms the first neuromasts of the posterior lateral line. This primordium travels at 1.5-1.7 somites/hour and deposits neuromast that are polarized along the antero-posterior axis.

name: secondary posterior lateral line primordium
description: Second lateral line primordium. These primordia moves at 0.2 somites/hour and deposite neromasts that are polarized in a dorso-ventral direction.

name: anterior lateral line primordium
description: A migrating group of cells originating from an anterior lateral line placode. The primordium deposits neuromasts and interneuromasts between them during its migration.

name: middle lateral line primordium
description: A migrating group of cells originating from the middle lateral line placode. The primordium deposits neuromasts with interneuromasts between them.

name: barbel primordium
description: A surface structure that will eventually grow to form a barbel. The primordium is rich in taste buds. The final location for taste buds present in the primordium is the distal tip of the mature barbel.

name: intestinal bulb epithelium
description: Intestinal epithelium which lines the lumen of the intestinal bulb.

name: primary dental epithelium
description: Epithelium that surrounds a primary tooth. This epithelium is committed to formation of replacement teeth.

name: ampullary nerve
description: A branch of the 8th cranial nerve that innervates the cristae ampullaris.

name: distal epidermal cap of regenerating fin/limb
description: Part of regeneration epithelium at the tip of the fin/limb [ZFA,modified].

name: basal regeneration epithelium of regenerating fin/limb
description: Layer of the wound epidermis that surrounds the blastema in the fin or limb[ZFA,modified].

name: extrahepatic duct
description: Bile duct that collects from the intrahepatic ducts and feeds into the common bile duct.

name: ventral liver lobe
description: Portion of the liver which develops on the fish's ventral side.
parents: BFO:0000050 some NCBITaxon:6072|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002107|RO:0002162 some (not (NCBITaxon:32523))|UBERON:0000481|UBERON:0004119

name: choroid plexus vascular circuit
description: Cranial vasculature where the posterior cerebral veins and the trans-choroid plexus branch form a circuit around the 4th ventricle choroid plexus.

name: inter-parietal joint
description: Fibrous joint connecting the parietal bones.

name: intervillus pockets
description: A portion of tissue formed between the base of the intestinal villi that is part of the intestinal epithelium where intestinal stem cells are located. In the intestine no crypts are present, but, the regions between the villi, the intervillus pockets, have a crypt-like function. Cells are produced in the intervillus pockets and shed from the villus tips.

name: continuous capillary
description: Capillary that has endothelial cells that provide an uninterrupted lining, and only allow small molecules, like water and ions to diffuse through tight junctions which leave gaps of unjoined membrane which are called intercellular clefts.

name: fenestrated capillary
description: Capillary that has pores in the endothelial cells (60-80 nm in diameter) that are spanned by a diaphragm of radially oriented fibrils and allow small molecules and limited amounts of protein to diffuse.

name: hyomandibula-opercle joint
description: Synovial joint that articulates the hyomandibula and the opercle.

name: pterotic fossa
description: Fossa on the pterotic where the hyomandibula articulates.

name: erector muscle
description: Muscle that moves parts of the body in a superior direction to an erect position. Antagonistic to depressor muscle.

name: preopercle horizontal limb-symplectic joint
description: Joint that articulates the posterior edge of the preopercle horizontal limb with the symplectic.

name: hypophyseal fenestra
description: Space enclosed by the trabeculae cranii. The anterior tip of the notochord extends into the posterior region of the hypophyseal fenestra.

name: depressor muscle
description: A muscle that moves body parts into an inferior direction or lowered position. Antagonistic to erector muscle.

name: immature gonad
description: Immature reproductive tissue that has not undergone final maturation into either testis or ovary. During gonadal development, the gonad may be transiently intersexual where there is a parallel presence of both oocytes and spermatocytes.

name: intestinal mucosal muscle
description: A thin layer of smooth muscle immediately beneath the base of the villi which permits the intestinal mucosa to dynamically move and fold.

name: hyomandibular foramen
description: Foramen in the hyomandibula that allows passage of the anterior lateral line nerve and the facial nerve (cranial nerve VII).

name: preopercle vertical limb-hyomandibula joint
description: Joint that articulates the anterior edge of the preopercle vertical limb and the hyomandibula.

name: enteric circular muscle
description: Smooth muscle of the enteric muscle system in which the cells are aligned perpendicular to the lumen of the gut.

name: distal late tubule
description: Portion of the renal tubule which is just posterior to the distal early tubule.

name: pronephric glomerular capsule epithelium
description: Simple squamous epithelium that lines the capsule of the pronephric glomerulus.

name: fin fold pectoral fin bud
description: Fin fold of the pectoral fin bud, resulting from mesenchyme migration into the apical fold.
parents: BFO:0000050 some NCBITaxon:6072|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0005419|RO:0002162 some (not (NCBITaxon:32523))|RO:0002202 some UBERON:0005421|UBERON:0000481|UBERON:0004121

name: pectoral fin fold
description: The functional webs of the paired fins. They arise as a consequence of apical fold (AER) expansion and of migration of the distal mesenchyme. The fin folds are delimited by a dorsal and a ventral striated epidermis. The cells of the epidermal basal stratum are positioned on a basement membrane. Directly beneath the basement membrane of each side there is an array of actinotrichs, fibers of the extracellular matrix which act as supportive elements of the larval fin folds.
parents: BFO:0000050 some NCBITaxon:6072|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000151|RO:0002202 some UBERON:2005316|UBERON:0000481|UBERON:0004121

name: posterior recess
description: Posterior protrusion of the third ventricle.

name: endohypothalamic tract
description: CNS white matter, axonal tract interconnecting catecholaminergic cell groups in the posterior tuberculum and hypothalamus.

name: extrapancreatic duct
description: Portion of the pancreatic duct, external to the pancreas body that connects the pancreas with the hepatopancreatic ampulla.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 1
description: Dorsal fin distal radial 1 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 2
description: Dorsal fin distal radial 2 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 3
description: Dorsal fin distal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 4
description: Dorsal fin distal radial 4 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 5
description: Dorsal fin distal radial 5 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 6
description: Dorsal fin distal radial 6 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 7
description: Dorsal fin distal radial 7 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin distal radial bone 8
description: Dorsal fin distal radial 8 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 3
description: Dorsal fin proximal radial 3 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 4
description: Dorsal fin proximal radial 4 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 5
description: Dorsal fin proximal radial 5 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 6
description: Dorsal fin proximal radial 6 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 7
description: Dorsal fin proximal radial 7 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: dorsal fin proximal radial bone 8
description: Dorsal fin proximal radial 8 element that is composed of bone tissue.

name: pars superior ear
description: The dorsal part of the ear. Comprises the three semicircular canals, which connect to the utricle.

name: pars inferior ear
description: The ventral portion of the ear. It contains the saccule and the laguena which are the primary auditory organs.

name: transverse canal
description: Duct that crosses the midline connecting the sacculi.

name: inner ear foramen
description: Foramen in the inner ear.

name: dorso-rostral cluster
description: Early-forming telencephalic neural cluster. Neurons of the dorso-rostral cluster (drc) extend axons to form the supra-optic tract (SOT) and the anterior commissure (AC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: ventro-rostral cluster
description: Early-forming neural cluster located in the rostral diencephalon. At 19 h, axons arising from the vrc grow caudally to pioneer the tract of the postoptic commissure (TPOC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: ventro-caudal cluster
description: Early-forming neural cluster of the ventral midbrain. At 16 h, axons of the vcc grow caudally to pioneer the medial longitudinal fasciculus (MLF), which is part of the larger ventral longitudinal tract (VLT). Later, neurons from this cluster project axons rostrally into the tract of the post-optic commissure (TPOC). Ross et al., 1992.

name: epiphysial cluster
description: Early-developing neuronal cluster of the epiphysis. By 24 hpf the pioneer axon of the dorsoventral diencephalic tract (DVDT) has arisen from the ec and grown ventrally. As this axon encounters axons of the TPOC, it makes a near-90 rostral turn and grows rostrally among axons of the TPOC growing in the opposite direction. Ross et al., 1992.

name: hemal prezygapophysis
description: Hemal prezygapophyses are paired, anteromedially directed processes arising from the bases of hemal arches, ligamentously joined to the hemal postzygapophyses of the preceding vertebra. Posterior caudal vertebrae close to the caudal fin lack hemal prezygopophyses.

name: preplacodal ectoderm
description: Non neural ectoderm that surrounds the presumptive neural plate and gives rise to neurogenic placodes.

name: hyohyoideus
description: Is a hyoid muscle that inserts at the most anterior basibranchial and also at the posterior ends of the ceratohyals and functions in jaw closure.

name: dorsal adductor hyomandibulae
description: Is a hyoid muscle that attaches to the dorsomedial faces of the hyosymplectics.

name: mineralized skeletal tissue
description: Skeletal tissue that is mineralized.

name: ganoine
description: Odontogenic tissue that is hypermineralized acellular, noncollagenous, covered by an epidermis and often deposited in multiple layers.

name: median fin
description: Fin that is an unpaired fin located in the sagittal plane of the organism.

name: anal fin
description: Median fin that is located posterior to the anus.

name: caudal fin
description: The caudal fin is the most posterior median fin. It is composed of a complex of modified centra and modified neural and hemal arches and spines.

name: anal fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton that is located posterior to the anus.

name: caudal fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton supporting the caudal fin.

name: dorsal fin skeleton
description: Median fin skeleton located on the dorsal surface of the organism.

name: median fin skeleton
description: Postcranial axial skeleton that is unpaired and located on the sagittal plane of the organism.

name: lepidotrichium
description: Dermal bone that is rod-like, formed and usually contained in a fin membrane, and jointed to or adjacent to distal radials. Lepidotrichia are formed from paired hemitrichia surrounding actinotrichia. There are usually two more lepidotrichia than distal radials.

name: pelvic fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the pelvic fin skeleton.

name: caudal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the caudal fin skeleton.

name: pectoral fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the pectoral fin skeleton.

name: anal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the anal fin skeleton.

name: dorsal fin lepidotrichium
description: Lepidotrichium that is part of the dorsal fin skeleton.

name: inter-clavicle joint
description: Joint that articulates left and right clavicles.

name: hypochordal lepidotrichium
description: Caudal fin lepidotrichium located ventral to the notochord.

name: ventral humeral ridge
description: A distinct bony ridge on ventralsurface of the humeral shaft that corresponds to the attachment site of the pectoralis muscle.

name: pedal centrale
description: A centrale found in the pes.

name: ectepicondylar flange
description: Flange present of the distal region of the humerus, associated with extensor musculature of forelimb.

name: flexor surface
description: Surface of a long bone that possess the flexor muscle attachment sites.

name: inner digits of foot
description: The medial most digits of the pes.

name: calcaneal tuber
description: An enlargement of the distal region of the calcaneum that corresponds to the attachment site for the foot extensor muscles.

name: preacetabular process
description: Process on ilium located anteriorly to acetabulum.

name: suprascapular fossa
description: Fossa on the medial surface on the scapula above the glenoid.

name: astragalus-calcaneum unit
description: Osteological unit consisting of the astragalus and calcaneum.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0009879|RO:0002180 some UBERON:0001450|RO:0002180 some UBERON:0002395|UBERON:0000075|UBERON:0004120

name: ascending process of the astragalus
description: Flattened process of the dorsl surface of the astragalus which contacts the tibia anteriorly.

name: suture
description: Line of junction between two parts immovably connected. Modified from Henderson's Dictionary of Biological Terms.

name: actinopterygian pyloric caecum
description: A finger-like out-pocketing of the intestine where it meets the end of the stomach (pylorus). Also spelled cecum (ceca). Serves to aid digestion.

name: precaudal vertebra
description: Vertebral bone lacking hemal spines (Weitzman, 1962), refers generally to the anterior vertebral region bounding the abdominal cavity. Alternate but not quite synonymous terms are abdominal or trunk vertebrae, which bear parapophyses and ribs. In many actinopterygians dorsal to the posterior abdominal cavity there are transitional vertebrae lacking ribs but also without hemal spines or sometimes even enclosed hemal arches. The primary definition would identify these vertebrae as precaudal. Bird and Mabee, 2003.

name: lateral occipital foramen
description: Foramen that has the exoccipital as the anterior and dorsal rim. The occipital forms the anterior rim during early development. [database_cross_reference: GOC:cvs][database_cross_reference: https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2244-7917][database_cross_reference: ZFIN:ZDB-PUB-961014-192].

name: arthropod tagma
description: One of the main divisions of the whole organism of arthropods formed from groups of segments.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000468|RO:0002160 some NCBITaxon:6656|RO:0002162 some (not (NCBITaxon:7742))|UBERON:0011676

name: insect ocular segment
description: Head segment derived from the second embryonic segment (between the labral and antennal segments). In the larva, this segment includes Bolwig's organ.

name: insect head segment
description: Any segment that is part of some insect head.

name: procephalic segment
description: A segment that is anterior to the gnathal segments.

name: labral segment
description: Procephalic segment anterior to the antennal segment. In the adult it bears the clypeo-labrum.

name: antennal segment
description: Segment anterior to the intercalary segment. In the adult it bears the antennae.

name: insect gnathal segment
description: The head segments that develop posterior to the embryonic/larval mouth.

name: insect labial segment
description: Most posterior of the gnathal segments. In the adult it bears a pair of fused appendages, the labia, and its ectodermal invaginations give rise to the salivary glands.

name: insect thorax
description: The main middle section of the insect body comprising three thoracic rings: the pro-, the meso- and the metathoraces which are more or less well fused and cask-like sometimes having on the upper lateral part one of two pairs of wings, while on the ventrolateral part each thoracic ring bears a pair of legs.

name: insect thoracic segment
description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some thorax (UBERON:6000015).

name: insect prothoracic segment
description: The first (most anterior) segment of the thorax.

name: insect mesothoracic segment
description: The second (middle) segment of the thorax.

name: insect metathoracic segment
description: The third (most posterior) segment of the thorax.

name: insect abdomen
description: The most posterior of the three tagma (UBERON:6000002).

name: insect abdominal segment
description: Metameric subdivision of the abdomen.

name: insect dorsal appendage
description: Paired appendage of the eggshell, located on the anterior-dorsal side of the egg, just posterior to the operculum. Functions as a respiratory structures.

name: insect anterior ectoderm
description: The region of the ectoderm anterior to the cephalic furrow.

name: insect trunk mesoderm
description: The mesoderm of segments T1-A9. It first becomes morphologically distinct during ventral furrow formation. Following invagination during stages 6 and 7, it remains a coherent structure with no morphologically apparent subdivisions, apart from transient metamery during stage 9, until stage 11. It undergoes a number of morphological changes during this period: as its cells divide following invagination, it loses its epithelial integrity and by stage 9 has rearranged into a monolayer of cuboidal cells. A further division happens during stage 10 leading to two distinct layers by stage 11.

name: embryonic tagma
description: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some embryo (UBERON:6000052).

name: insect embryonic segment
description: Any insect segment that is part of some embryo.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000922|RO:0002160 some NCBITaxon:50557|RO:0002162 some NCBITaxon:6656|UBERON:0000914

name: insect embryonic head segment
description: Any segment that is part of some insect embryonic head.

name: insect embryonic procephalic segment
description: Any procephalic segment (UBERON:6000007) that is part of some embryonic head (UBERON:6000155) in an insect.

name: insect embryonic antennal segment
description: Any antennal segment (UBERON:6000009) that is part of some embryonic head (UBERON:6000155).

description: Any gnathal segment (UBERON:6000011) that is part of some embryonic head (UBERON:6000155).

name: insect embryonic labial segment
description: Any labial segment (UBERON:6000014) that is part of some embryonic head (UBERON:6000155).

name: insect embryonic thorax
description: Any thorax (UBERON:6000015) that is part of some embryo (UBERON:6000052).

description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some embryonic thorax (UBERON:6000166).

name: insect embryonic prothoracic segment
description: Prothoracic segment of the embryo.

name: insect embryonic mesothoracic segment
description: Mesothoracic segment of the embryo.

name: insect embryonic metathoracic segment
description: Metathoracic segment of the embryo.

name: insect embryonic abdomen
description: Abdomen of the embryo.

name: insect embryonic abdominal segment
description: Metameric subdivision of the embryonic abdomen.

name: insect embryonic abdominal segment 8
description: Any abdominal segment 8 (UBERON:6000029) that is part of some embryonic abdomen (UBERON:6000171).

name: insect embryonic abdominal segment 9
description: Any abdominal segment 9 (UBERON:6000030) that is part of some embryonic abdomen (UBERON:6000171).

name: insect presumptive embryonic/larval nervous system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval nervous system.

name: insect presumptive embryonic/larval central nervous system
description: The sum of all the structures in the embryo that will develop into the embryonic/larval central nervous system.

name: insect embryonic brain
description: Brain of the embryo.

name: insect proneural cluster
description: An equivalence group of the neurectoderm where all cells can, although only one will, become a neural progenitor cell.

name: insect embryonic imaginal precursor
description: Embryonic structure that will proliferate during larval development into a larval imaginal disc. During early embryogenesis the precursor is part of the epithelial sheet before segregating from the epithelial sheet by late embryogenesis (Bate and Martinez Arias, 1991).

name: insect imaginal disc primordium
description: Population of contiguous, morphologically distinct cells that will form an imaginal disc.

name: insect labial disc primordium
description: Primordium that will form the labial disc.

name: insect eye-antennal disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the eye-antennal disc develops.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000922|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:6000160|RO:0002202 some UBERON:6005533|UBERON:6001649

name: insect genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the genital disc develops.

name: insect male genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the male genital disc derives.

name: insect female genital disc primordium
description: Primordium from which the female genital disc derives.

name: insect embryonic/larval circulatory system
description: Tubular system of the embryo/larva through which hemolymph flows.
parents: BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0000323|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:0002548|RO:0002160 some NCBITaxon:50557|UBERON:0001009

name: insect embryonic/larval lymph gland
description: Hematopoietic organ of the larva, located along the dorsal vessel, behind the brain. It produces the plasmatocytes, crystal cells and lamellocytes which are released at the end of the larval instar and onset of metamorphosis. It is composed of 3 pairs of bilateral lobes: an anterior primary lobe, a posterior secondary lobe and the most posterior lobe (or multiple lobes), the tertiary lobe. Each lobe is separated by pericardial cells. In the late embryo, the lymph gland consists of a single pair of lobes (primary lobes) containing around 20 cells each that flank the dorsal vessel. By the second larval instar, the lymph gland is composed of two or three new pairs of posterior lobes, and the primary lobes have increased in size to contain around 200 cells. During the first and early second larval instars, the lymph gland comprises only the hematopoietic progenitor population. The lymph gland increases in size ten-fold by the late third instar, and at this stage the progenitor cells (prohemocytes) become restricted to the medial region (medullary zone) of the primary lobe and become quiescent. The differentiated hemocytes are found in the periphery (cortical zone) of the primary lobe and these cells proliferate extensively. The posterior signalling center is a group of about 30 cells at the posterior tip of the primary lobe that secretes several signalling molecules and functions as a stem-cell niche. The secondary and tertiary lobes contain prohemocytes, and rarely a differentiated cell. Lymph glands are eliminated at metamorphosis.
parents: BFO:0000050 some NCBITaxon:6072|BFO:0000050 some UBERON:6001664|RO:0002202 some UBERON:6000132|RO:0002202 some UBERON:6005467|UBERON:0000481|UBERON:0004120

name: insect ring gland
description: A closely associated cluster of three neuroendocrine glands located anterior to the aorta and dorsal to the esophagus. At embryonic stage 17 and in larva it is found anterior to the brain and is formed by the corpus cardiacum ventrally, the prothoracic gland laterally and the corpus allatum dorsally. The adult ring gland is located anterior to the proventriculus and is formed by the corpus cardiacum ventrally, the corpus allatum dorsally and the hypocerebral ganglion posterior to the corpus cardiacum. It is innervated by neurons of the nervus corporis cardiaci (NccI-III).

description: Any tagma (UBERON:6000002) that is part of some larva (UBERON:6001727).

description: Any segment that is part of some larva.

description: Any ocular segment (UBERON:6000005) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

description: Any segment that is part of some larval head.

description: Any procephalic segment (UBERON:6000007) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

description: Any labral segment (UBERON:6000008) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

description: Any antennal segment (UBERON:6000009) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

description: Any gnathal segment (UBERON:6000011) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

description: Any labial segment (UBERON:6000014) that is part of some larval head (UBERON:6001730).

description: Any thorax (UBERON:6000015) that is part of some larva (UBERON:6001727).

description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some larval thorax (UBERON:6001741).

name: insect larval prothoracic segment
description: Any prothoracic segment (UBERON:6000017) that is part of some larval thorax (UBERON:6001741).

description: Any mesothoracic segment (UBERON:6000018) that is part of some larval thorax (UBERON:6001741).

description: Any metathoracic segment (UBERON:6000019) that is part of some larval thorax (UBERON:6001741).

description: Any abdomen (UBERON:6000020) that is part of some larva (UBERON:6001727).

description: Any segment (UBERON:6000003) that is part of some larval abdomen (UBERON:6001746).

description: Any abdominal segment 8 (UBERON:6000029) that is part of some larval abdomen (UBERON:6001746).
